l%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22200%2B%20Senior%20Economists%20Ask%20UN%2C%20World%20Bank%20to%20Act%20Against%20Extreme%20Global%20Inequalities%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F18100156%2Fatul-pandey-0f3bZHXZSz8-unsplash.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3EA%20group%20of%20236%20senior%20economists%20from%20across%20the%20world%20have%20written%20to%20United%20Nations%20secretary-general%20Antonio%20Guterres%20and%20World%20Bank%20president%20Ajay%20Banga%2C%20asking%20that%20they%20work%20to%20reduce%20extreme%20inequalities%20across%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20letter%20has%20been%20authored%20by%20Nobel%20prize%20winner%20and%20professor%20at%20Columbia%20University%20Joseph%20Stiglitz%20and%20professor%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Massachusetts%20Amherst%20Jayati%20Ghosh%2C%20and%20signed%20by%20economists%20from%2067%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20know%20that%20high%20inequality%20undermines%20all%20our%20social%20and%20environmental%20goals%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20letter%20states.%20%E2%80%9C%E2%80%A6Goals%20matter.%20Leadership%20matters.%20The%20Bank%20and%20UN%20SDGs%20are%20uniquely%20placed%20to%20offer%20the%20rallying%20call%20for%20a%20reduction%20in%20inequality%20that%20our%20divided%20world%20needs%20so%20urgently%20today.%20We%20ask%20you%20to%20seize%20this%20opportunity%20to%20back%20stronger%20goals%20and%20better%20metrics%20for%20both%20wealth%20and%20income%2C%20as%20well%20as%20wage%20shares%20of%20national%20income.%20Also%2C%20SDG10%20is%20not%20a%20separate%2C%20standalone%20goal%3A%20all%20economic%2C%20financial%2C%20and%20social%20policies%20should%20be%20assessed%20in%20terms%20of%20their%20likely%20impact%20on%20this%20goal.%20This%20would%20clearly%20signal%20our%20collective%20ambition%20to%20forge%20a%20more%20equal%20world.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERead%20the%20full%20text%20of%20the%20letter%20below.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A7%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDear%20Secretary-General%20of%20the%20United%20Nations%20Antonio%20Guterres%20and%20President%20of%20the%20World%20Bank%20Ajay%20Banga%2C%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20group%20of%20economists%20and%20leaders%20in%20the%20fight%20against%20extreme%20inequalities%20from%20around%20the%20world%2C%20we%20write%20to%20request%20your%20leadership%20towards%20ensuring%20that%20the%20United%20Nations%20Sustainable%20Development%20Goals%20and%20the%20World%20Bank%20back%20vital%20new%20strategic%20goals%20and%20indicators%2C%20that%20can%20redouble%20efforts%20to%20address%20rising%20extreme%20inequality.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20are%20living%20through%20a%20time%20of%20extraordinarily%20high%20economic%20inequality.%20Extreme%20poverty%20and%20extreme%20wealth%20have%20risen%20sharply%20and%20simultaneously%20for%20the%20first%20time%20in%2025%20years.%20Between%202019%20and%202020%2C%20global%20inequality%20grew%20more%20rapidly%20than%20at%20any%20time%20since%20WW2.%20The%20richest%2010%25%20of%20the%20global%20population%20currently%20takes%2052%25%20of%20global%20income%2C%20whereas%20the%20poorest%20half%20of%20the%20population%20earns%208.5%25%20of%20it.%20Billions%20of%20people%20face%20the%20terrible%20hardship%20of%20high%20and%20rising%20food%20prices%20and%20hunger%2C%20whilst%20the%20number%20of%20billionaires%20has%20doubled%20in%20the%20last%20decade.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20know%20that%20high%20inequality%20undermines%20all%20our%20social%20and%20environmental%20goals.%20The%202006%20World%20Development%20Report%2C%20as%20well%20as%20multiple%20other%20studies%2C%20have%20shown%20that%20extreme%20inequality%20of%20the%20kind%20we%20are%20observing%20today%20has%20a%20destructive%20effect%20on%20society.%20It%20corrodes%20our%20politics%2C%20destroys%20trust%2C%20hamstrings%20our%20collective%20economic%20prosperity%20and%20weakens%20multilateralism.%20We%20also%20know%20that%20without%20a%20sharp%20reduction%20in%20inequality%2C%20the%20twin%20goals%20of%20ending%20poverty%20and%20preventing%20climate%20breakdown%20will%20be%20in%20clear%20conflict.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202015%2C%20all%20the%20governments%20of%20the%20world%20made%20history%20by%20setting%20themselves%20a%20Sustainable%20Development%20Goal%20to%20reduce%20inequalities%20%E2%80%93%20%E2%80%9CSDG10%E2%80%9D.%20Yet%20since%20then%2C%20following%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic%20and%20now%20the%20global%20cost%20of%20living%20crisis%20inequalities%20have%20worsened%2C%20by%20many%20measures.%C2%A0%20SDG10%20remains%20largely%20ignored.%20Equally%20troubling%2C%20the%20main%20SDG10%20target%2C%20based%20on%20the%20World%20Bank%E2%80%99s%20Shared%20Prosperity%20goal%2C%20does%20not%20adequately%20measure%20or%20monitor%20key%20aspects%20of%20inequality.%C2%A0%20Evidence%20from%20household%20surveys%20shows%20that%20one%20in%20five%20countries%20showing%20a%20positive%20trend%20in%20Shared%20Prosperity%20simultaneously%20saw%20inequality%20by%20other%20measures%2C%20like%20the%20Palma%20Ratio%2C%20increase%2C%20including%20countries%20such%20as%20Mongolia%2C%20Chile%20and%20Vietnam.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20summer%20we%20have%20a%20critical%20opportunity%20to%20strengthen%20our%20resolve%20to%20reduce%20this%20deep%20divide%20and%20send%20a%20clear%20signal%20to%20people%20around%20the%20world%20that%20the%20institutions%20designed%20to%20serve%20them%20are%20serious%20about%20ending%20this%20crisis%20of%20extreme%20inequality.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20must%20strengthen%20our%20existing%20goals.%20We%20must%20act%20this%20summer%20to%20secure%20agreement%20that%20the%20UN%20SDG%2010%20must%20also%20have%20strengthened%20targets%20and%20better%20metrics%2C%20looking%20at%20inequalities%20both%20between%20countries%20and%20within%20them%20by%20using%20indicators%20that%20track%20wealth%20as%20well%20as%20income%20inequality.%20We%20are%20pleased%20that%20the%20World%20Bank%20is%20reviewing%20its%20Shared%20Prosperity%20goal.%20The%20new%20leadership%20of%20the%20World%20Bank%20has%20a%20tremendous%20opportunity%20to%20strengthen%20this%20goal%20to%20assess%20inequalities%20across%20the%20entire%20spectrum%20of%20the%20income%20and%20wealth%20distribution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20have%20been%20significant%20advances%20in%20inequality%20data%2C%20such%20as%20more%20accurate%20estimates%20of%20top%20incomes%2C%20helping%20to%20enable%20a%20new%20generation%20of%20policy%20making%20rooted%20in%20a%20clear%20distributional%20analysis%20of%20the%20impact%20of%20policy%20changes.%C2%A0%20These%20need%20to%20be%20systematised%20and%20pushed%20further%2C%20to%20enable%20high-level%20inequality%20analysis%20by%20every%20government.%20This%20will%20be%20the%20only%20way%20to%20ensure%20broad%20political%20consensus%20for%20the%20transformation%20our%20economies%20must%20make%20to%20a%20zero-carbon%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGoals%20matter.%20Leadership%20matters.%20The%20Bank%20and%20UN%20SDGs%20are%20uniquely%20placed%20to%20offer%20the%20rallying%20call%20for%20a%20reduction%20in%20inequality%20that%20our%20divided%20world%20needs%20so%20urgently%20today.%20We%20ask%20you%20to%20seize%20this%20opportunity%20to%20back%20stronger%20goals%20and%20better%20metrics%20for%20both%20wealth%20and%20income%2C%20as%20well%20as%20wage%20shares%20of%20national%20income.%20Also%2C%20SDG10%20is%20not%20a%20separate%2C%20standalone%20goal%3A%20all%20economic%2C%20financial%2C%20and%20social%20policies%20should%20be%20assessed%20in%20terms%20of%20their%20likely%20impact%20on%20this%20goal.%20This%20would%20clearly%20signal%20our%20collective%20ambition%20to%20forge%20a%20more%20equal%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYours%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-table%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Ctable%3E%5Cn%3Ctbody%3E%5Cn%3Ctr%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E%3Cstrong%3EID%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E%3Cstrong%3EName%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3Ctd%3E%3Cstrong%3ERole%20