022%2C%20many%20countries%20feared%20a%20famine.%20In%20Africa%20and%20the%20Middle%20East%20in%20particular%2C%20a%20hunger%20crisis%20threatened.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFood%20prices%20had%20already%20risen%20before%20the%20start%20of%20the%20Ukraine%20war%2C%20but%20the%20Russian%20invasion%20made%20them%20skyrocket%20worldwide.%20In%20addition%2C%20the%20Russian%20blockade%20of%20the%20Black%20Sea%20meant%20millions%20of%20tons%20of%20grain%20were%20stuck%20in%20Ukrainian%20silos%2C%20in%20danger%20of%20rotting.%20According%20to%20the%20European%20Union%20%E2%80%9Cmaintaining%20Ukrainian%20grain%20supplies%20remains%20critical%20to%20global%20food%20security.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20could%20happen%20if%20the%20deal%20expires%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20Russia%20does%20not%20agree%20to%20extending%20the%20deal%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20unclear%20whether%20Ukraine%20will%20continue%20to%20ship%20the%20same%20quantities%20of%20grain%20to%20the%20world.%20The%20high%20cost%20of%20insuring%20the%20ships%20could%20be%20a%20major%20problem.%20Ships%20that%20want%20to%20cross%20the%20Black%20Sea%20already%20have%20to%20be%20insured%20for%20thousands%20of%20dollars.%20Shipping%20companies%20might%20be%20reluctant%20to%20send%20their%20ships%20through%20the%20war%20zone%20if%20there%20is%20no%20Russian%20approval.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETransporting%20grain%20overland%20could%20also%20become%20difficult.%20Since%20the%20beginning%20of%20the%20war%2C%20Ukraine%20has%20exported%20large%20quantities%20of%20grain%20via%20eastern%20EU%20countries%20%E2%80%94%20but%20there%20are%20too%20few%20freight%20carriages%20to%20export%20all%20of%20Ukraine%E2%80%99s%20grain%20over%20land.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%2C%20farmers%20in%20some%20eastern%20EU%20countries%20resent%20Ukrainian%20supplies%20being%20shipped%20through%20their%20countries%2C%20saying%20it%20undercuts%20local%20supplies%20and%20effectively%20takes%20away%20markets%20for%20their%20own%20crops.%20In%20reaction%2C%20the%20European%20Union%20imposed%20import%20restrictions%20earlier%20this%20month%20that%20stipulate%20grain%20can%20be%20transported%20through%20Bulgaria%2C%20Hungary%2C%20Poland%2C%20Romania%20and%20Slovakia%20but%20cannot%20be%20sold%20in%20these%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20does%20the%20current%20deal%20work%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20agreement%20regulates%20grain%20exports%20from%20the%20Ukrainian-controlled%20Black%20Sea%20ports%20of%20Odesa%2C%20Chornomorsk%20and%20Pivdenny.%20Ships%20must%20cross%20the%20Black%20Sea%20along%20an%20agreed%20humanitarian%20sea%20corridor%20toward%20Istanbul.%20Ships%20en%20route%20to%20and%20from%20Ukrainian%20ports%20are%20checked%20at%20a%20Turkish-controlled%20base%20by%20a%20special%20team%20of%20Russian%2C%20Turkish%2C%20Ukrainian%20and%20UN%20inspectors.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETwo%20UN%20task%20forces%20ensure%20that%20Ukrainian%20grain%20can%20be%20shipped%20across%20the%20Black%20Sea%2C%20and%20they%20also%20facilitate%20the%20export%20of%20Russian%20food%20and%20fertilizer%20products.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F02%2F20165942%2F51905521463_0600c20141_k.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F02%2F20165942%2F51905521463_0600c20141_k.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F02%2F20165942%2F51905521463_0600c20141_k-300x200.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F02%2F20165942%2F51905521463_0600c20141_k-1024x683.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-641263%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22800%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EA%20protest%20against%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine.%20Photo%3A%20pix-4-2-day%2FFlickr%20CC%20BY%20NC%20ND%202.0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20successful%20was%20the%20agreement%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Black%20Sea%20Grain%20Initiative%20and%20EU%20solidarity%20corridors%20to%20support%20Ukrainian%20exports%20have%20helped%20food%20prices%20fall%20and%20stabilize.%20More%20than%2030%20million%20tons%20of%20grain%20and%20other%20food%20products%20have%20been%20exported%20up%20to%20May%202023%20thanks%20to%20the%20agreement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPoorer%20countries%2C%20in%20particular%2C%20have%20benefited%3A%20Around%2064%25%20of%20wheat%20went%20to%20developing%20countries%2C%20while%20corn%20was%20exported%20almost%20equally%20to%20developed%20and%20developing%20countries.%20In%20March%2C%20though%2C%20several%20media%20outlets%20reported%20that%20less%20and%20less%20grain%20was%20being%20shipped%20from%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAfrican%20nations%20push%20for%20Ukraine%20peace%20settlement%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOverall%20food%20exports%20made%20possible%20by%20the%20agreement%20fell%20by%20about%20three-quarters%20in%20May%20compared%20with%20October%20last%20year%2C%20as%20more%20shipping%20companies%20shied%20away%20from%20sending%20ships%20on%20the%20dangerous%20route.%20But%20strict%20regulations%20also%20make%20it%20difficult%20for%20ships%20to%20pass%20through%20quickly.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20UN%20secretary-general%20is%20disappointed%20by%20the%20slowing%20pace%20of%20inspections%20and%20the%20exclusion%20of%20the%20port%20of%20Yuzhny%2FPivdennyi%20from%20the%20Black%20Sea%20Initiative%2C%E2%80%9D%20Guterres%E2%80%99%20deputy%20spokesperson%2C%20Farhan%20Haq%2C%20said%20in%20a%20statement%20on%20Tuesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Russian%20side%20has%20been%20complaining%20that%20its%20demands%20are%20not%20being%20met%20and%20that%20Western%20sanctions%20are%20hindering%20the%20export%20of%20its%20own%20agricultural%20products.%20President%20Vladimir%20Putin%20argued%20to%20an%20African%20peace%20delegation%20earlier%20this%20week%20that%20the%20grain%20agreement%20did%20not%20solve%20the%20problems%20African%20countries%20had%20with%20high%20global%20food%20prices%2C%20because%20only%203%25%20of%20Ukraine%E2%80%99s%20grain%20exports%20go%20to%20the%20poorest%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20important%20is%20the%20Black%20Sea%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Black%20Sea%20is%20a%20strategic%20crossroads%20between%20southeastern%20Europe%20and%20Asia%2C%20a%20region%20where%20maritime%2C%20continental%2C%20geostrategic%20and%20economic%20interests%20come%20together.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20the%20only%20opportunity%20for%20Ukraine%20to%20export%20its%20grain%20to%20the%20world%20by%20sea.%20Access%20to%20the%20open%20sea%2C%20and%20thus%20an%20opportunity%20to%20access%20other%20export%20routes%2C%20is%20only%20possible%20via%20the%20Dardanelles%20and%20the%20Bosporus%20%E2%80%94%20both%20straits%20controlled%20by%20Turkey.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECountries%20that%20border%20the%20Black%20Sea%20have%20an%20interest%20in%20the%20routes%20but%20the%20inland%20sea%20also%20plays%20a%20large%20economic%20role%20for%20China.%20As%20part%20of%20Beijing%E2%80%99s%20New%20Silk%20Road%20project%2C%20the%20sea%20route%20across%20the%20Black%20Sea%20is%20supposed%20to%20allow%20for%20a%20better%20Chinese-European%20flow%20of%20goods.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%2C%20originally%20written%20in%20German%2C%20appeared%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Frussia-pulls-out-of-ukraine-grain-deal-whats-next%2Fa-65994255%5C%22%3EDW%3C%2Fa%3E%20first.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689652377000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F18092056%2F51301760656_9e4322a5ea_c.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%