t%20resolve%2C%20and%20the%20distance%20did%20not%20help.%20They%20haven't%20been%20speaking%20and%20are%20separated%2C%20and%20a%20divorce%20is%20likely%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20outlet%20reported.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENotably%2C%20Ariana%20Grande%20and%20Dalton%20Gomez%20got%20married%20in%202021%20at%20her%20home%20in%20Montecito%20in%20a%20private%20ceremony.%20The%20two%20got%20engaged%20months%20before%20their%20marriage%20and%20spent%20a%20lot%20of%20time%20together%20during%20the%20Covid-19%20pandemic.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELast%20year%2C%20the%20singer%20shared%20a%20makeup%20tutorial%20on%20TikTok%20where%20she%20wasn't%20wearing%20a%20ring%2C%20however%2C%20she%20shut%20down%20rumours%20immediately.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20just%20not%20wearing%20my%20wedding%20ring%2C%20it's%20getting%20cleaned.%20I'm%20not%20getting%20a%20divorce%20before%20you%20start%2C%20don't%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%20at%20the%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20as%20per%20%3Cem%3EPeople%3C%2Fem%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMore%20recently%2C%20this%20year%20on%20Valentine's%20Day%2C%20Gomez%20shared%20some%20loving%20photos%20featuring%20Grande.%20%26quot%3BMy%20forever%20valentine%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20captioned%20the%20post.%20Grande%20also%20reshared%20the%20pic%20and%20added%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20love%20you%26quot%3B%20with%20a%20heart.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20%3Cem%3EPeople%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20since%20getting%20together%2C%20Grande%20and%20Gomes%20have%20largely%20kept%20their%20relationship%20out%20of%20the%20spotlight.%20But%20Grande%20did%20share%20a%20rare%20glimpse%20last%20November%20when%20she%20shared%20a%20pair%20of%20photos%20of%20Gomes%20as%20part%20of%20a%20carousel%20on%20Instagram.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689648540000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-07%2Famnhjmbg_ariana-grande-dalton-gomez_625x300_18_July_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Ffeature%2Fariana-grande-dalton-gomez-separated-and-heading-for-divorce-after-2-years-of-marriage-report-4217054%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Pop%20singer%20Ariana%20Grande%20and%20husband%20Dalton%20Gomez%20are%20reportedly%20splitting%20up%20after%20two%20years%20of%20marriage%2C%20American%20weekly%20magazine%20People%20reported.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Ffeature%2Fariana-grande-dalton-gomez-separated-and-heading-for-divorce-after-2-years-of-marriage-report-4217054%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Ffeature%2Fariana-grande-dalton-gomez-separated-and-heading-for-divorce-after-2-years-of-marriage-report-4217054%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Ffeature%2Fariana-grande-dalton-gomez-separated-and-heading-for-divorce-after-2-years-of-marriage-report-4217054%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22A%20Montana%20couple%20spent%20%2420%2C000%20building%20a%202-bedroom%20house%2C%20and%20now%20they're%20debt-free.%20There's%20just%20one%20catch%3A%20The%20house%20is%20made%20of%20clay%2C%20sand%2C%20and%20straw.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221168%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20house%20made%20from%20earth%20and%20dirt%20rises%20from%20the%20ground%20in%20the%20distance%2C%20behind%20a%20lush%2C%20green%20vegetable%20garden.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64af9ff34031de0019eae1f1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22876%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20exterior%20of%20the%20completed%20cob%20house%20and%20the%20garden.%3Cp%3EDaniel%20Ray%2FSpiritwood%20Natural%20Building%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EA%20Montana%20couple%20spent%20over%202%20years%20building%20their%20700-square-foot%20cob%20house%20by%20hand.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EDaniel%20Ray%2C%20the%20owner%2C%20estimates%20that%20they%20spent%20less%20than%20%2420%2C000%20on%20the%20entire%20construction.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ENow%2C%20the%20couple%20runs%20a%20business%20hosting%20workshops%20to%20teach%20others%20how%20to%20build%20their%20own%20sustainable%20houses.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EBuilding%20an%20earthen%20home%20from%20scratch%20might%20sound%20daunting%20to%20some%2C%20but%20for%20Daniel%20and%20Katherine%20Ray%2C%20it's%20their%20way%20of%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Montana%20couple%2C%20who%20started%20dating%20in%20high%20school%2C%20first%20came%20across%20cob%20houses%20when%20they%20were%20in%20college.%20Cob%20is%20a%20natural%20building%20material%20made%20out%20of%20clay%2C%20sand%2C%20and%20straw.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20stumbled%20across%20a%20photo%20of%20a%20cob%20house%20in%20Wales%20and%20we%20got%20really%20interested%2C%20so%20we%20started%20collecting%20lots%20of%20pictures%20of%20other%20people's%20cob%20houses.%20It%20was%20a%20pot-shot%20dream%20that%20we%20really%20wanted%20to%20do%2C%26quot%3B%20Ray%20told%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222146%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20smiling%20couple%20with%20their%20child.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64abba388ed31300199e3ddf%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221609%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDaniel%20and%20Katherine%20Ray%20with%20their%20child%2C%20seated%20outside%20their%20cob%20house.%3Cp%3EDaniel%20Ray%2FSpiritwood%20Natural%20Building%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20it%20wasn't%20until%20a%20couple%20of%20years%20later%20that%20the%20couple%20finally%20had%20a%20chance%20to%20turn%20it%20into%20reality.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAfter%20we%20completed%20college%2C%20we%20moved%20to%20Vancouver%2C%20British%20Columbia%2C%20so%20I%20could%20finish%20my%20master's%20degree%20in%20library%20science%2C%26quot%3B%20Ray%20said.%20%26quot%3BAfter%20we%20moved%20back%20to%20Montana%2C%20I%20didn't%20have%20a%20job%20lined%20up%20yet%2C%20and%20we%20were%20renting%20%E2%80%94%20so%20we%20thought%20it%20would%20be%20the%20perfect%20time%20to%20build%20a%20cob%20house.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERay's%20parents%20owned%20an%20empty%20acre%20of%20land%20that%20used%20to%20be%20a%20horse%20pasture%2C%20and%20they%20granted%20the%20couple%20permission%20to%20build%20on%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAnd%20so%20we%20did.%20Our%20first%20home%20was%20like%20a%20300-square-foot%20cob%20house%20on%20their%20property%2C%26quot%3B%20Ray%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EAfter%20three%20years%2C%20the%20couple%20decided%20they%20wanted%20to%20build%20a%20bigger%20home%20on%20land%20that%20they%20owned.%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20saw%20their%20first%20cob%20house%20as%20practice%20for%20the%20new%20space%20they%20had%20in%20mind.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERay%20and%20his%20wife%20purchased%20a%20plot%20of%20land%20in%20the%20Bitterroot%20Valley%20in%20Victor%2C%20Montana%2C%20and%20started%20building%20their%20second%20cob%20house%20in%20the%20spring%20of%202016.%20They%20did%20not%20share%20how%20much%20they%20paid%20for%20the%20land.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222448%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Wooden%20beams%20and%20other%20markings%20are%20made%20on%20the%20excavated%20ground%20to%20denote%20where%20the%20house%20should%20go.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64ae564c94be880019f3868c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221836%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20ground%20had%20to%20be%20excavated%20before%20the%20couple%20could%20start%20building%20their%20house.%3Cp%3EDaniel%20Ray%2FSpiritwood%20Natural%20Building%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20a%20massive%20undertaking%3A%20The%20couple%20spent%20almost%20three%20years%20trying%20to%20complete%20the%20project%20by%20hand%2C%20Ray%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20both%20had%20full-time%20jobs%20and%20then%20would%20also%20work%20about%2040%20hours%20a%20week%20on%20building%20the%20house%2C%26quot%3B%20Ray%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20was%20a%20lot%20of%20work%20for%20over%20two%20years.%20I%20mean%2C%20if%20somebody%20was%20able%20to%20take%20a%20couple%20of%20years%20off%20to%20build%20their%20house%2C%20they'd%20probably%20be%20able%20to%20do%20it%20a%20lot%20quicker%20than%20us%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20couple%20was%20involved%20in%20every%20part%20of%20the%20construction%20process.%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20only%20did%20they%20design%20the%20blueprints%20for%20the%20house%2C%20but%20they%20were%20also%20responsible%20for%20sourcing%20the%20natural%20materials%20required%20to%20build%20the%20structure.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20couple%20used%20their%20feet%20to%20make%20cob%20by%20mixing%20dirt%2C%20clay%2C%20straw%2C%20and%20water.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22640%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20person%20stepping%20on%20a%20mix%20of%20dirt%2C%20hay%2C%20and%20water%20to%20create%20cob.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64afbdd5c22d1a0019453c5d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22480%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECob%20is%20made%20using%20water%2C%20straw%2C%20and%20dirt%20that%20has%20a%20high%20amount%20of%20clay%20content.%20To%20mix%20it%2C%20the%20mixture%20is%20trampled%20on%20by%20foot.%3Cp%3EDaniel%20Ray%2FSpiritwood%20Natural%20Building%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTo%20make%20cob%2C%20you%20basically%20take%20dirt%20that%20has%20a%20solid%20amount%20of%20clay%20content%20%E2%80%94%20which%20is%20usually%20anywhere%20from%2030%20to%2050%25%20clay%20%E2%80%94%20and%20you%20mix%20with%20water%20until%20it's%20a%20good%20mud-like%20consistency%20before%20you%20add%20straw%2C%26quot%3B%20Ray%20said.%20%26quot%3BYou%20stomp%20it%20all%20together%2C%20so%20you're%20just%20mixing%20it%20on%20tarps%20with%20your%20feet.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20of%20the%20building%20materials%20needed%20were%20sourced%20locally%2C%20Ray%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAll%20of%20the%20straw%20that%20we%20used%20for%20the%20walls%20is%20from%20the%20area.%20All%20of%20the%20soil%2C%20which%20is%20the%20main%20component%20of%20the%20walls%2C%20is%20from%20a%20quarry%20that's%20about%20five%20miles%20away%20from%20the%20house%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnlike%20bricks%2C%20which%20have%20to%20be%20held%20together%20by%20mortar%2C%20the%20walls%20of%20a%20cob%20house%20are%20built%20upwards%20in%20a%20single%20layer%2C%20Ray%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20walls%20are%20just%20one%20full%20solid%20piece%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20process%20of%20building%20a%20cob%20house%20is%20quite%20similar%20to%20building%20a%20regular%20home.%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20the%20walls%20could%20be%20constructed%2C%20the%20couple%20had%20to%20first%20excavate%20the%20ground%20to%20make%20space%20for%20the%20foundation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22640%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20person%20stacking%20layers%20of%20cob%20up%20to%20create%20the%20walls%20of%20the%20house.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64abb7a66d7e02001af89b56%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22480%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20walls%20of%20the%20cob%20house%20are%20built%20in%20layers.%3Cp%3EDaniel%20Ray%2FSpiritwood%20Natural%20Building%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20rented%20a%20small%20excavator%2C%20dug%20the%20foundation%20out%2C%20and%20then%20we%20just%20started%20building%20from%20the%20ground%20up%2C%26quot%3B%20Ray%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20just%20like%20a%20normal%20stick-frame%20house%20or%20anything%20like%20that.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20the%20couple%20had%20experience%20from%20building%20their%20previous%20cob%20home%2C%20the%20two%20of%20them%20aren't%20professionally%20trained%20in%20construction.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20both%20graduated%20with%20anthropology%20degrees%2C%20and%20I%20have%20a%20master's%20in%20library%20and%20information%20science%2C%20so%20I'm%20really%20good%20at%20doing%20research%2C%26quot%3B%20Ray%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20had%20zero%20contracting%20experience.%20Neither%20of%20us%20had%20built%20anything%20really%2C%20other%20than%20cabinets%20and%20stuff%20like%20that.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThankfully%2C%20family%20members%20chipped%20in%20to%20help%20whenever%20they%20could%2C%20which%20meant%20that%20they%20didn't%20have%20to%20hire%20any%20external%20contractors%2C%20he%20added.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EDepending%20on%20the%20location%20where%20the%20cob%20house%20is%20constructed%2C%20building%20permits%20might%20be%20required.%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223264%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Two%20men%20placing%20window%20frames%20into%20gaps%20in%20the%20cob%20walls.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64abb7a18ed31300199e3db1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222448%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAssembling%20the%20windows.%3Cp%3EDaniel%20Ray%2FSpiritwood%20Natural%20Building%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%20where%20we're%20located%2C%20there%20are%20not%20very%20many%20building%20codes%20or%20permitting%20required%20%E2%80%94%20that's%20kind%20of%20the%20reason%20that%20we%20chose%20the%20area%20as%20well%2C%26quot%3B%20Ray%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20that's%20not%20to%20say%20that%20people%20can't%20build%20cob%20houses%20in%20areas%20with%20stricter%20rules%2C%20he%20said.%20They%20still%20can%20%E2%80%94%20as%20long%20as%20they%20have%20an%20architect%20to%20sign%20off%20on%20their%20plans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20big%20thing%20is%20you'd%20have%20to%20get%20those%20permits%20to%20have%20a%20bank%20give%20you%20a%20loan%20to%20build%20a%20house.%20But%20if%20you're%20building%20a%20house%20for%20so%20cheap%2C%20you%20don't%20necessarily%20need%20a%20bank%20to%20loan%20you%20money%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20couple%20learned%20how%20to%20build%20their%20cob%20house%20using%20books%20and%20online%20resources.%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222448%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20person%20working%20on%20shaping%20the%20internal%20walls%20and%20features%20of%20the%20house%20using%20cob.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64abb7b76d7e02001af89b61%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221836%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EEven%20internal%20features%20such%20as%20shelves%20and%20seats%20are%20made%20using%20cob.%3Cp%3EDaniel%20Ray%2FSpiritwood%20Natural%20Building%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20really%20had%20three%20books%20that%20were%20our%20guiding%20principles%20for%20building%2C%26quot%3B%20Ray%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20the%20main%20idea%20is%20that%20anybody%20could%20build%20a%20house%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20not%20rocket%20science.%20There%20are%20a%20lot%20of%20specialized%20construction%20industries%20that%20make%20people%20feel%20like%20they%20can't%20when%20it's%20actually%20something%20that%20they%20can%20do.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20though%20earthen%20houses%20are%20commonly%20found%20in%20countries%20like%20Mexico%20and%20India%2C%20this%20building%20method%20hasn't%20quite%20taken%20off%20in%20the%20same%20way%20in%20the%20US%2C%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ESince%20the%20couple's%20cob%20house%20has%20a%20large%20floor%20area%2C%20three%20wooden%20posts%20are%20used%20to%20support%20a%20center%20beam%20that%20holds%20up%20the%20roof.%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222448%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20part%20of%20the%20roof%20has%20been%20assembled%20and%20placed%20on%20top%20of%20the%20cob%20house.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64abb7b36d7e02001af89b5c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221836%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWooden%20posts%20are%20used%20to%20support%20the%20roof.%3Cp%3EDaniel%20Ray%2FSpiritwood%20Natural%20Building%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20this%20is%20a%20feature%20that%20a%20smaller