-farm-water%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Washington%20Post%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported%20the%20state%20has%20let%20the%20company%20Fondomonte%20Arizona%20pull%20groundwater%20from%20leased%20land%20west%20of%20Phoenix%20for%20almost%20a%20decade%20in%20order%20to%20irrigate%20their%20alfalfa%20hay.%20The%20alfalfa%20was%20then%20exported%20to%20Saudi%20Arabia%20and%20used%20to%20feed%20dairy%20cows.%20The%20land%20was%20leased%20under%20a%20state%20program%20that%20allows%20companies%20to%20rent%20state-owned%20lands%20to%20grow%20crops.%20And%20while%20it's%20not%20the%20only%20company%20to%20lease%20state%20land%20in%20this%20way%2C%20the%20foreign%20ownership%20has%20caused%20outrage%20in%20the%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20according%20to%20the%20Post%2C%20the%20state%20had%20no%20idea%20exactly%20how%20much%20water%20Fondomonte%20was%20actually%20using%20after%20a%20proposal%20to%20track%20its%20usage%20failed.%20John%20Schneeman%2C%20one%20of%20the%20state%20planners%20involved%2C%20told%20the%20outlet%20state%20officials%20were%20%26quot%3Bcautious%20of%20tangling%20with%20a%20powerful%20company.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Post%20investigation%20found%20the%20water%20amounted%20to%20enough%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Farizona-saudi-arabia-fondomonte-butler-valley-water-residents-cut-off-2023-7%5C%22%3Esupport%20a%20city%20of%2050%2C000%20people%3C%2Fa%3E.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20Arizona%20residents%20have%20been%20asked%20to%20cut%20back%20their%20water%20consumption.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFondomonte%20has%20said%20it's%20been%20unfairly%20singled%20out%20and%20that%20they%20should%20be%20measured%20by%20the%20same%20standards%20as%20all%20farming%20leaseholders%20in%20the%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20news%20was%20especially%20striking%20given%20the%20fraught%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcalifornia-western-states-disagree-colorado-river-cuts-proposal-borrowed-water-2023-2