A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Mercury%20Hits%20New%20Highs%20As%20Heatwaves%20Scorch%20The%20Globe%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3ETemperatures%20reached%20new%20highs%20on%20Monday%20as%20heatwaves%20and%20wildfires%20scorched%20swathes%20of%20the%20Northern%20Hemisphere%2C%20forcing%20the%20evacuation%20of%201%2C200%20children%20close%20to%20a%20Greek%20seaside%20resort.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHealth%20authorities%20have%20sounded%20alarms%20from%20North%20America%20to%20Europe%20and%20Asia%2C%20urging%20people%20to%20stay%20hydrated%20and%20shelter%20from%20the%20burning%20sun%2C%20in%20a%20stark%20reminder%20of%20the%20effects%20of%20global%20warming.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENear%20Athens%2C%20a%20forest%20fire%20flared%20in%20strong%20winds%20by%20the%20popular%20beach%20town%20of%20Loutraki%20where%20the%20mayor%20said%20holiday%20camps%20for%20youngsters%20had%20come%20under%20threat.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20saved%201%2C200%20children%20who%20were%20in%20the%20holiday%20camps%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20mayor%20Giorgos%20Gkionis.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEmergency%20services%20were%20also%20battling%20wildfires%20in%20Kouvaras%20and%20the%20resorts%20of%20Lagonissi%2C%20Anavyssos%20and%20Saronida%20near%20Athens.%20Several%20homes%20were%20burned%20in%20the%20area%2C%20according%20to%20footage%20from%20public%20broadcaster%20ERT.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20extreme%20weather%20...%20is%20having%20a%20major%20impact%20on%20human%20health%2C%20ecosystems%2C%20economies%2C%20agriculture%2C%20energy%20and%20water%20supplies%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20World%20Meteorological%20Organization%20(WMO)%20Secretary-General%20Petteri%20Taalas.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20underlines%20the%20increasing%20urgency%20of%20cutting%20greenhouse%20gas%20emissions%20as%20quickly%20and%20as%20deeply%20as%20possible.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E'We%20thought%20we'd%20escape'%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Rome%2C%20where%20temperatures%20hit%20a%20near-record%2039C%20on%20Monday%2C%20American%20Colman%20Peavy%20could%20not%20believe%20the%20heat%20as%20he%20sipped%20a%20cappuccino%20at%20a%20cafe%20with%20his%20wife%20Ana%20at%20the%20start%20of%20a%20two-week%20vacation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20from%20Texas%20and%20it's%20really%20hot%20there%2C%20we%20thought%20we%20would%20escape%20the%20heat%20but%20it's%20even%20hotter%20here%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20the%2030-year-old.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20already%20the%20world's%20hottest%20June%20on%20record%2C%20according%20to%20the%20EU%20weather%20monitoring%20service%2C%20and%20July%20looks%20to%20be%20readying%20to%20challenge%20its%20own%20record.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChina%20reported%20a%20new%20high%20for%20mid-July%20in%20the%20northwest%20of%20the%20country%2C%20where%20temperatures%20reached%2052.2C%20in%20the%20Xinjiang%20region's%20village%20of%20Sanbao%2C%20breaking%20the%20previous%20high%20of%2050.6C%20set%20six%20years%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHeatstroke%20alerts%20had%20been%20issued%20in%2032%20out%20of%20Japan's%2047%20prefectures%2C%20mainly%20in%20central%20and%20southwestern%20regions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20least%2060%20people%20were%20treated%20for%20heatstroke%2C%20media%20reported%2C%20including%2051%20taken%20to%20hospital%20in%20Tokyo.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Cyprus%2C%20where%20temperatures%20are%20expected%20to%20remain%20above%2040C%20through%20Thursday%2C%20a%2090-year-old%20man%20died%20as%20a%20result%20of%20heatstroke%20and%20three%20other%20seniors%20were%20hospitalised%2C%20health%20officials%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E'Oppressive'%20US%20heat%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20western%20and%20southern%20US%20states%2C%20which%20are%20used%20to%20high%20temperatures%2C%20more%20than%2080%20million%20people%20were%20under%20advisories%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bwidespread%20and%20oppressive%26quot%3B%20heatwave%20roasted%20the%20region.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECalifornia's%20Death%20Valley%2C%20often%20among%20the%20hottest%20places%20on%20Earth%2C%20reached%20a%20near-record%2052C%20Sunday%20afternoon.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Arizona%2C%20state%20capital%20Phoenix%20tied%20its%20record%20of%2018%20consecutive%20days%20above%2043C%20(109F)%2C%20as%20temperatures%20hit%2045C%20(113F)%20early%20Monday%20afternoon.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20National%20Weather%20Service%20predicts%20similar%20highs%20at%20least%20through%20Sunday%2C%20while%20warning%20of%20overnight%20lows%20remaining%20dangerously%20elevated%2C%20above%2032C%20(90F).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20used%20to%20110%2C%20112%20(degrees%20Fahrenheit)...%20But%20not%20the%20streaks%2C%26quot%3B%20Nancy%20Leonard%2C%20a%2064-year-old%20retiree%20from%20the%20nearby%20suburb%20of%20Peoria%2C%20told%20AFP.%20%26quot%3BYou%20just%20have%20to%20adapt.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Southern%20California%2C%20several%20wildfires%20have%20ignited%20over%20the%20past%20few%20days%20in%20rural%20areas%20east%20of%20Los%20Angeles.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20biggest%2C%20named%20the%20Rabbit%20Fire%2C%20had%20burned%20nearly%208%2C000%20acres%20and%20was%2035%20percent%20contained%20on%20Monday%20morning%2C%20according%20to%20authorities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20neighbouring%20Canada%2C%20882%20wildfires%20were%20active%20on%20Monday%2C%20including%20579%20considered%20out%20of%20control%2C%20authorities%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESmoke%20from%20the%20fires%20has%20descended%20on%20the%20United%20States%20again%2C%20prompting%20air%20quality%20alerts%20across%20much%20of%20the%20northeast.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHistoric%20highs%20forecast%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Europe%2C%20Italians%20were%20warned%20to%20prepare%20for%20%26quot%3Bthe%20most%20intense%20heatwave%20of%20the%20summer%20and%20also%20one%20of%20the%20most%20intense%20of%20all%20time%26quot%3B%2C%20with%20a%20red%20alert%20issued%20for%2016%20cities%20including%20Rome%2C%20Bologna%20and%20Florence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpain%20enjoyed%20little%20reprieve%20with%20temperatures%20of%2047C%20in%20the%20southern%20town%20of%20Villarrobledo.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlong%20with%20the%20heat%2C%20parts%20of%20Asia%20have%20also%20been%20battered%20by%20torrential%20rain.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESouth%20Korea's%20president%20vowed%20Monday%20to%20%26quot%3Bcompletely%20overhaul%26quot%3B%20the%20country's%20approach%20to%20extreme%20weather%2C%20after%20at%20least%2040%20people%20were%20killed%20in%20recent%20flooding%20and%20landslides%20during%20monsoon%20rains%2C%20which%20are%20forecast%20to%20continue%20through%20Wednesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(This%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20auto-generated%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689647400000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-07%2Fsosket9o_heatwave-afp_625x300_18_July_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fmercury-hits-new-highs-as-heatwaves-scorch-the-globe-4217046%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Temperatures%20reached%20new%20highs%20on%20Monday%20as%20heatwaves%20and%20wildfires%20scorched%20swathes%20of%20the%20Northern%20Hemisphere%2C%20forcing%20the%20evacuation%20of%201%2C200%20children%20close%20to%20a%20Greek%20seaside%20resort.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A7%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fmercury-hits-new-highs-as-heatwaves-scorch-the-globe-4217046%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fmercury-hits-new-highs-as-heatwaves-scorch-the-globe-4217046%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fmercury-hits-new-highs-as-heatwaves-scorch-the-globe-4217046%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Vande%20Sadharan%3F%20Railways%E2%80%99%20new%20train%20for%20common%20man%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689646770000%2C%22visual%2