C%20can%20be%20vanquished%20in%20next%20year%E2%80%99s%20court%20of%20the%20people.%20And%2C%20though%20the%20opposition%20political%20landscape%20remains%20extremely%20untidy%2C%20it%20still%20has%20a%20Carlos%20Alcaraz%20up%20its%20sleeve.%20His%20name%20is%20Mallikarjun%20Kharge.%20If%20the%20opposition%20leaders%20play%20the%20game%20intelligently%2C%20India%20could%20have%20its%20first%20Dalit%20prime%20minister%20next%20May.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20messiness%20of%20the%20opposition%E2%80%99s%20unity%20or%20lack%20of%20it%20revolves%20round%20the%20vexatious%20issue%20of%20leadership.%20That%20issue%2C%20itself%2C%20is%20predicated%20on%20a%20few%20givens.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFirst%2C%20no%20non-Congress%20political%20party%20can%20win%20more%20than%2040%20Lok%20Sabha%20seats%20on%20its%20own%2C%20and%20therefore%20cannot%20lay%20any%20claim%20to%20prime%20ministerial%20leadership.%20Nor%20would%20such%20a%20claim%20be%20conceded%20by%20anyone.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESecond%2C%20while%20the%20centrality%20of%20the%20Congress%20party%20to%20any%20non-BJP%2C%20non-Modi%20alternative%20is%20beyond%20question%2C%20the%20opposition%20leaders%20will%20not%20countenance%20any%20suggestion%20of%20Rahul%20Gandhi%20as%20their%20joint%20prime%20ministerial%20face.%20There%20are%20too%20many%20bad%20memories%20and%20too%20much%20of%20bad%20blood%20between%20the%20Gandhis%20and%20the%20other%20political%20leaders%20for%20even%20a%20sullen%20acceptance%20of%20his%20stewardship.%20And%2C%20the%20Congress%20too%20returns%20the%20favour.%20It%20simply%20will%20not%20be%20amenable%20to%20have%20a%20Mamta%20Banerjee%20or%20an%20Arvind%20Kejriwal%20as%20prime%20minister.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22281%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F04%2F04192003%2Fstatecraft.png%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-237577%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22233%5C%22%3EThird%2C%20notwithstanding%20all%20the%20enthusiasm%20and%20front-page%20headlines%20about%20and%20since%20the%20Bharat%20Jodo%20Yatra%2C%20Rahul%20Gandhi%20has%20yet%20to%20cross%20the%20threshold%20of%20acceptability.%20He%20remains%20an%20eccentric%20political%20persona.%20The%20middle%20classes%20will%20not%20back%20his%20prime%20ministerial%20claims%20simply%20because%20of%20his%20surname.%20The%20long%20and%20short%20of%20it%20is%20that%20India%20is%20not%20prepared%20to%20trade%20a%20Narendra%20Modi%20for%20a%20Rahul%20Gandhi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdmittedly%2C%20Rahul%20Gandhi%20is%20a%20very%20big%20elephant%20in%20the%20room.%20There%20are%20powerful%2C%20vested%20interests%20around%20him%20and%20these%20individuals%20have%20become%20used%20to%20exercising%20power%20without%20authority%20within%20the%20Congress%3B%20they%20would%20be%20less%20than%20excited%20about%20any%20stratagem%20that%20would%20take%20away%20the%20limelight%20from%20their%20principal.%20And%2C%20the%20same%20goes%20for%20his%20sister%2C%20Priyanka%20Gandhi%20Vadra.%20Her%20own%20sense%20of%20entitlement%20remains%20insatiable%20and%20untamed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20Rahul%20Gandhi%20has%20made%20it%20abundantly%20clear%20that%20he%20is%20not%20at%20all%20interested%20in%20the%20nitty-gritty%20of%20running%20a%20big%20organisation%2C%20leave%20alone%20the%20vast%20Union%20government.%20He%20is%20not%20wired%20to%20be%20a%20manager%2C%20even%20though%20he%20craves%20the%20trappings%20of%20a%20%E2%80%98supreme%20leader.%E2%80%99%20Like%20his%20mother%2C%20he%20has%20no%20appetite%20for%20the%20grinding%20and%20messy%20business%20of%20organisational%20chores%20and%20protocols%20and%20procedures.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHow%20then%20can%20the%20opposition%20leaders%20reconcile%20themselves%20to%20a%20Congress%20leadership%2C%20while%20coming%20to%20terms%20with%20their%20own%20limited%20numbers%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPerhaps%2C%20a%20non-Gandhi%20at%20the%20helm%20of%20a%20Congress-led%20coalition%20would%20appear%20to%20be%20not%20only%20the%20most%20feasible%20but%20also%20the%20most%20saleable%20answer.%20Hence%2C%20the%20importance%20of%20Mallikarjun%20Kharge.%20He%20has%20proved%20himself%20to%20be%20a%20sober%2C%20if%20unflamboyant%2C%20leader%20of%20a%20faction-ridden%20Congress%20party.%20If%20he%20does%20not%20sparkle%20with%20brilliance%2C%20he%20does%20exhibit%20qualities%20of%20being%20a%20reconciliator%20and%20a%20purveyor%20of%20common%20sense.%20The%20very%20anti-thesis%20to%20Narendra%20Modi%20and%20a%20healthy%20and%20desirable%20antidote%20at%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYoung%20leaders%20like%20Akhilesh%20Yadav%20or%20Tejashvi%20Yadav%20or%20an%20Arvind%20Kejriwal%20or%20even%20Mamta%20Banerjee%20may%20calculate%20that%20they%20would%20be%20better%20off%20with%20a%20Kharge%20arrangement%20than%20trying%20to%20survive%20another%20five%20years%20of%20the%20Modi-Shah%20%3Cem%3Edadagiri%3C%2Fem%3E.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%20%3C%2Fspan%3EBy%20now%20it%20should%20be%20clear%20to%20every%20regional%20leader%20in%20the%20country%20that%20there%20is%20a%20relentless%20logic%20to%20the%20Modi-Shah-Yogi%20combine%20that%20would%20mow%20down%20any%20and%20all%20regional%20players%2C%20friend%20or%20foe.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%20%3C%2Fspan%3EThere%20may%20still%20be%20a%20few%20like%20a%20Naveen%20Patnaik%20or%20Chandra%20Babu%20Naidu%20or%20a%20Sukhbhir%20Badal%20who%20think%20that%20they%20have%20the%20elbow%20room%20to%20buy%20peace%20with%20the%20ruling%20cabal%3B%20but%20their%20survival%20would%20entirely%20be%20on%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20terms.%20And%20Modi%20can%20dictate%20those%20terms%20only%20as%20long%20as%20he%20appears%20to%20be%20the%20winning%20horse.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EModi%E2%80%99s%20credentials%20as%20a%20champion%20of%20the%20poor%2C%20the%20have-nots%20and%20the%20underclasses%20acquired%20a%20sharp%20cutting%20edge%20only%20because%20his%20image-managers%20cleverly%20pitted%20him%20against%20an%20%E2%80%98entitled%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98privileged%E2%80%99%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%20%3C%2Fspan%3ERahul%20Gandhi.%20All%20these%20advantages%20get%20blunted%20if%20Modi%20has%20a%20face%20off%20against%20a%20Dalit%20leader%20like%20Mallikarjun%20Kharge.%20If%20Modi%20benefitted%20from%20being%20thought%20of%20as%20the%20first%20%E2%80%98OBC%E2%80%99%20prime%20minister%2C%20then%20the%20entire%20Ambedkarite%20constituency%20can%20be%20expected%20to%20get%20galvanised%20at%20the%20prospect%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20first%20Dalit%20prime%20minister.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20simple%20challenge%20before%20the%20opposition%20leaders%20is%20to%20reassure%20the%20nation%20that%20collectively%20they%20have%20the%20wisdom%20and%20the%20collegiate%20skills%20to%20give%20India%20a%20stable%20and%20sensitive%20governing%20arrangement.%20There%20is%20no%20need%20for%20super-strong%20and%20overweening%20prime%20ministers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20possible%20to%20suggest%20that%20India%20has%20had%20its%20fill%20of%20%E2%80%9Cdecisive%20government%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Cstrong%20leaders.%E2%80%9D%20The%20opposition%20leaders%20will%20have%20to%20educate%20the%20masses%20about%20the%20flaws%20and%20failures%20of%20the%20past%20ten%20years.%20Modi%20talked%20big%2C%20promised%20to%20stare%20down%20the%20Chinese%20with%20his%20%3Cem%3E%E2%80%98lal%20aankh%E2%80%99%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20and%20ended%20up%20inviting%20aggression.%20China%E2%80%99s%20troops%20are%20now%20ensconced%20on%20much%20more%20Indian%20territory%20than%20they%20had%20access%20to%20during%20the%20previous%20%E2%80%98weak%E2%80%99%20regimes.%20Pakistan%20remains%20as%20intractable%20as%20ever%2C%20the%20Kashmiris%20remain%20sullen%20and%20unreconciled%20to%20New%20Delhi%E2%80%99s%20overlordship%2C%20and%20there%20are%20daily%20reminders%20that%20the%20entire%20North-East%20has%20been%20spectacularly%20mismanaged%20by%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98strong%E2%80%99%20government%20in%20New%20Delhi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20all%20the%20exaggerated%20talk%20of%20the%20fight%20against%20corruption%20and%20the%20corrupt%2C%20no%20citizen%20can%20possibly%20affirm%20that%20India%20is%20less%20%E2%80%98corrupt%E2%80%99%20than%20it%20was%20in%202014.%20If%20anything%2C%20given%20the%20exponential%20outbreak%20in%20crony%20capitalism%2C%20it%20is%20obvious%20that%20in%20all%20BJP-administered%20states%20corruption%20has%20become%20the%20%E2%80%98new%20normal.%E2%80%99%20The%20sale%20and%20purchase%20of%20public%20offices%20and%20elected%20legislators%20is%20now%20palmed%20off%20as%20normal%20or%20even%20virtuous%20%E2%80%93%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%20%3C%2Fspan%3Eas%20%3Ci%3E%E2%80%98Chanakaya%20niti%E2%80%99%3C%2Fi%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20ten%20years%20of%20presiding%20over%20a%20transactional%20regime%2C%20Modi%20is%20no%20longer%20the%20messiah%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98common%20man.%E2%80%99%20He%20is%20vulnerable%20to%20the%20charge%20of%20being%20the%20%3Ci%3Emukhota%3C%2Fi%3E%20or%20mask%20of%20the%20global%20and%20super-rich%20Indian%20elites%2C%20though%20he%20still%20has%20the%20%E2%80%9Cmandir%E2%80%9D%20card%20up%20his%20sleeve.%20To%20begin%20with%2C%20opposition%20leaders%20have%20to%20summon%20the%20requisite%20astuteness%20to%20realise%20that%20Modi%20can%20be%20dislodged%20only%20by%20a%20challenge%20from%20a%20new%20social%20coalition%2C%20led%20by%20a%20Dalit.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689643924000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F12%2F14153024%2F2022_12img14_Dec_2022_PTI12_14_2022_RPT061B.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Findia-can-have-its-first-dalit-prime-minister-in-2024%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22After%20running%20a%20transactional%20regime%20for%2010%20years%2C%20Modi%20is%20no%20longer%20the%20messiah%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98common%20man.%E2%80%99%20His%20credentials%20as%20a%20champion%20of%20the%20poor%20were%20based%20on%20being%20pitted%20against%20an%20%E2%80%98entitled%E2%80%99%20Rahul%20Gandhi.%20All%20these%20advantages%20get%20blunted%20if%20he%20faces%20off%20against%20a%20Dalit%20leader%20like%20Mallikarjun%20Kharge.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Findia-can-have-its-first-dalit-prime-minister-in-2024%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22How%20the%20Dravidian%20Model%20of%20Development%20Succeeded%20in%20Tamil%20Nadu%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F17200916%2F18015946060_e7c39e240b_k.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhen%20I%20was%20doing%20ethnographic%20fieldwork%20towards%20an%20anthropology%20of%20cinema%20during%202005-07%20in%20the%20villages%20of%20Tamil%20Nadu%2C%20I%20became%20increasingly%20convinced%20of%20what%20many%20of%20us%20held%20as%20some%20kind%20of%20commonsensical%20understanding%3A%20That%20Tamil%20Nadu%20had%20primed%20itself%20for%20more%20inclusive%20development%20and%20greater%20redistribution%20through%20participatory%20governance%20when%20liberalisation%20and%20globalisation%20accelerated%20economic%20activity%20in%20the%20early%201990s.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EReading%20A.%20Kalaiyarasan%20and%20M.%20Vijayabaskar%E2%80%99s%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Dravidian%20Model%3A%20Interpreting%20Political%20Economy%20of%20Tamil%20Nadu%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Eone%20feels%20as%20if%20one%20is%20meeting%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20a%20conceptual%20jungle%20with%20people%20who%20had%20travelled%20into%20it%20from%20the%20other%20side.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhat%20the%20much-awaited%20book%20presents%20is%20a%20thorough%20and%20insightful%20compilation%20of%20hard%20data%20on%20development%20indicators%20that%20calls%20for%20an%20explanation%20of%20the%20political%20processes%20that%20served%20as%20causal%20factors%2C%20which%20the%20authors%20undertake%20with%20a%20zest%20that%20is%20scholarly%20and%20erudite%20yet%20accessible%20to%20the%20non-specialist.%C2%A0%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ECase%20for%20the%20subnational%20variant%C2%A0%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Dravidian%20Model%20makes%20a%20compelling%20case%20for%20an%20interpretive%20schema%20of%20development%20that%20integrates%20processes%20of%20political%20mobilisation%20by%20reading%20it%20as%20a%20key%20subnational%20variant%20within%20India.%20The%20Dravid%20Munnetra%20Kazhagam%20(DMK)%20mobilised%20people%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20the%20broad%20egalitarian%2C%20anti-caste%2C%20social%20justice%20themes%20which%20go%20by%20the%20tag%20%E2%80%98Dravidianism%E2%80%99%20and%20the%20composite%20identity%20of%20Dravidian-Tamil.%20On%20coming%20to%20power%20in%201967%2C%20the%20%E2%80%98Dravidian%E2%80%99%20state%20took%20key%20policy%20decisions%20focussing%20on%20everyday%20aspects%20of%20governance%20that%20included%20planning%20and%20delivery%2C%20all%20cumulatively%20determining%20the%20process%20of%20economic%20development%20in%20a%20certain%20manner.%20This%20is%20what%20qualifies%20it%20to%20be%20studied%20as%20a%20model.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20AIADMK%20which%20branched%20out%20of%20and%20alternated%20in%20power%20with%20the%20DMK%20in%20Tamil%20Nadu%20offered%20both%20continuity%20and%20variation%20to%20the%20policies%20pursued%20by%20the%20DMK%2C%20a%20point%20that%20is%20repeatedly%20made%20in%20the%20book.%20The%20developmental%20yields%20of%20the%20rule%20of%20the%20two%20parties%20are%20well%20documented%20in%20the%20book%20in%20eight%20succinct%20chapters.%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20252px)%2085vw%2C%20252px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F17123716%2F71RYtmAraWL._SY385_.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22252%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F17123716%2F71RYtmAraWL._SY385_.jpg%20252w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F17123716%2F71RYtmAraWL._SY385_-196x300.jpg%20196w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-663556%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22385%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EA.%20Kalaiyarasan%2C%20M.%20Vijayabaskar%2C%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Dravidian%20Model%3A%20Interpreting%20Political%20Economy%20of%20Tamil%20Nadu%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20Cambridge%20University%20Press%20(2021)%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20first%20chapter%20makes%20the%20case%20for%20the%20need%20to%20study%20the%20subnational%20variant.%20Per%20capita%20income%20in%20Tamil%20Nadu%20that%20was%20nearly%20at%20the%20level%20of%20the%20national%20average%20in%201960-61%20became%20more%20than%20150%25%20of%20the%20national%20average%20by%202010-11.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20the%20reduction%20in%20both%20rural%20and%20urban%20poverty%20levels%20is%20also%20dramatic.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EFrom%20being%20more%20than%20the%20national%20average%2C%20it%20came%20down%20to%20being%20the%20third%20lowest%20in%20the%20country%2C%20less%20than%20Maharashtra%20and%20Gujarat%20which%20record%20greater%20per%20capita%20income.%20Hence%2C%20economic%20growth%20with%20reduction%20in%20levels%20of%20inequality%20places%20the%20Dravidian-Tamil%20subnational%20variant%20as%20a%20rewarding%20object%20of%20study.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20second%20chapter%20provides%20a%20rich%20theoretical%20look%20at%20the%20political%20mobilisation%20that%20developed%20a%20certain%20common%20sense%20in%20which%20redistribution%20was%20seen%20as%20the%20political%20norm%20with%20a%20sense%20of%20entitlement%20pervading%20the%20common%20people.%20The%20third%20and%20fourth%20chapters%20present%20the%20strides%20made%20in%20education%20and%20health%20%E2%80%93%20key%20sectors%20of%20exemplary%20achievement%20compared%20to%20most%20other%20Indian%20states.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20fifth%20chapter%20%E2%80%93%20a%20vital%20one%20%E2%80%93%20speaks%20of%20the%20broad-basing%20of%20growth%20and%20democratisation%20of%20capital%20that%20is%20followed%20by%20a%20study%20of%20rural%20transformation%20and%20urban%20labour%20in%20the%20sixth%20and%20seventh%20chapters.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20final%20chapter%20looks%20at%20the%20limits%20and%20pitfalls%20of%20the%20processes%20so%20that%20we%20have%20a%20balanced%20picture.%20Their%20attention%20to%20limits%20appears%20superfluous%20at%20times%2C%20in%20being%20discursive%20rather%20than%20demonstrative%2C%20like%20the%20allusion%20to%20essentialisation%20of%20the%20identity%20of%20the%20ruling%20elite%20suggested%20by%20Rosanvallon%2C%20which%20is%20not%20supported%20by%20empirical%20data%20or%20evidence.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20Tamil%20Nadu%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%98%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Es%20context%2C%20such%20allusion%20to%20essentialisation%20will%20only%20point%20to%20the%20empirical%20reduction%20of%20caste%20identity%20and%20the%20discursive%20fetishisation%20of%20the%20same%2C%20instead%20of%20focussing%20on%20the%20hegemonic%20and%20ideological%20implications%20of%20the%20caste%20system%20that%20the%20Dravidian%20model%20sought%20to%20dismantle%20%E2%80%93%20and%20which%20is%20the%20implicit%20theme%20of%20the%20book.%20This%20theme%20in%20fact%20connects%20to%20the%20much%20more%20expansive%20fusion%20of%20capital%20and%20ideology%20undertaken%20by%20Thomas%20Piketty%20on%20a%20global%20scale.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ELocal%20history%2C%20global%20design%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20am%20persuaded%20that%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Dravidian%20Model%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E(DM)%20is%20best%20read%20in%20conjunction%20with%20Piketty%E2%80%99s%20voluminous%20snapshots%20of%20the%20anthropological%2C%20structural-functional%20dimensions%20of%20world%20historical%20transformations%20on%20a%20global%20scale%20appropriately%20titled%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ECapital%20and%20Ideology%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20(CI).%20While%20the%20comparison%20of%20development%20indicators%20makes%20DM%20primarily%20rest%20on%20the%20comparison%20with%20the%20performance%20of%20other%20Indian%20states%2C%20the%20study%20of%20the%20ideological%20moorings%20of%20Dravidian%20political%20economy%20is%20best%20studied%20in%20the%20paradigm%20developed%20by%20Piketty.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20DM%20refers%20to%20CI%20in%20key%20moments%2C%20owing%20to%20its%20focus%20on%20the%20story%20of%20development%20in%20Tamil%20Nadu%20in%20empirical%20and%20conceptual%20terms%2C%20it%20does%20not%20connect%20to%20the%20speculative%20expanse%20of%20CI.%20On%20his%20part%2C%20Piketty%2C%20being%20aware%20of%20the%20primarily%20European%20template%20of%20his%20global%20analysis%2C%20makes%20the%20effort%20to%20pay%20attention%20to%20variations%20in%20India%2C%20China%20and%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20world.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPiketty%20refers%20to%20Tamil%20Nadu%20and%20even%20Periyar%20through%20a%20reading%20of%20the%20works%20of%20Nicholas%20Dirks%20and%20also%20to%20sub%20national%20variations%20in%20Indian%20postcolonial%20developmental%20history%20through%20reference%20to%20Amartya%20Sen%20and%20Jean%20Dreze%20but%20he%20stops%20with%20citing%20Kerala%20as%20an%20example.%20Hence%20the%20Periyar-inspired%20Dravidian%20model%20as%20a%20key%20variant%20of%20the%20global%20modes%20of%20transition%20will%20surely%20better%20inform%20his%20framework%20of%20analysis.%20Hence%20the%20proposition%20that%20DM%20and%20CI%20need%20to%20be%20read%20in%20conjunction.%20I%20will%20briefly%20present%20my%20case%20as%20to%20why%20this%20is%20inherently%20necessary.%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20task%20undertaken%20by%20DM%20is%20to%20show%20that%20the%20sub-national%20variant%20in%20the%20developmental%20path%20produced%20in%20Tamil%20Nadu%20is%20the%20product%20of%20Dravidian%20political%20ideology.%20As%20we%20have%20seen%2C%20this%20variant%20mitigates%20the%20trend%20to%20rising%20inequality%20seen%20all%20over%20the%20world%20and%20ensures%20effective%20redistribution%20through%20state%20measures.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIf%20this%20process%20is%20to%20be%20translated%20into%20the%20paradigm%20of%20capitalist%20transition%20that%20Piketty%20uses%2C%20it%20is%20possible%20to%20say%20that%20the%20Dravidian%20movement%20intervened%20in%20the%20transition%20of%20a%20society%20dominated%20by%20clergy%20and%20nobility%20to%20that%20of%20an%20ownership%20society%20resulting%20in%20the%20hegemony%20of%20the%20propertied%20class%20which%20once%20again%20accentuates%20inequality%20after%20a%20brief%20hiatus%20of%20reduction%20in%20inequality%20with%20the%20advent%20of%20democracy%20or%20social%20democracy.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Dravidian%20formation%20was%20able%20to%20intervene%20and%20preserve%20the%20moment%20of%20hiatus%20by%20forging%20left%20populism%20that%20countered%20the%20ideology%20of%20the%20clergy%2C%20in%20this%20instance%20Aryan%20Brahminism%2C%20which%20had%20subsumed%20the%20nobility%20and%20landed%20gentry%20in%20medieval%20and%20early%20modern%20Tamil%20Nadu%20in%20the%20iron%20grip%20of%20an%20exploitative%20caste%20order.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20prioritising%20the%20counter%20hegemonic%20articulations%20of%20the%20%3Cem%3Eplebes%3C%2Fem%3E%20against%20the%20exploitative%20Brahminical%20social%20order%20%E2%80%93%20the%20disenfranchised%20sections%20of%20the%20ternary%20society%20in%20Piketty%E2%80%99s%20terms%20%E2%80%93%20for%20a%20fair%20share%20in%20economic%20growth%20and%20governance%2C%20Dravidianism%20evolved%20a%20new%20common%20sense%20of%20equity%20as%20the%20bedrock%20of%20popular%2C%20electoral%20democracy.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20could%20effectively%20counteract%20the%20emerging%20stranglehold%20of%20the%20still%20evolving%20new%20propertied%20class%20and%20their%20liberal%20ideology%20on%20the%20state%20and%20governmental%20measures.%20This%20became%20possible%20only%20because%20the%20term%20Dravidian%20stood%20for%20repudiation%20of%20the%20Brahminic%20casteist%20ideology.%20The%20rigour%20of%20the%20critical%20idiom%20forged%20against%20the%20old%20ternary%20or%20quaternary%20society%20of%20Aryanism%2C%20which%20Dravidian%20politics%20sought%20to%20dismantle%2C%20continues%20to%20animate%20the%20politics%20of%20the%20plebes%20in%20the%20era%20of%20globalisation%2Fliberalisation.%20This%20analysis%20is%20the%20contribution%20DM%20makes%20to%20CI.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDM%20rightfully%20makes%20the%20contribution%20since%20in%20the%20very%20beginning%20of%20his%20account%2C%20Piketty%2C%20in%20listing%20the%20variety%20of%20theories%20about%20ethnic%20origins%20of%20dominant%20and%20dominated%20groups%2C%20which%20was%20used%20both%20to%20legitimise%20and%20delegitimise%20inequality%2C%20mentions%3A%20%E2%80%9C%E2%80%A6In%20India%2C%20nobles%20were%20said%20to%20be%20of%20Aryan%20origin%2C%20the%20commoners%20Dravidian.%E2%80%9D%20This%20is%20the%20precise%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Eraison%20d%E2%80%99etre%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20of%20the%20Dravidian%20model.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20a%20more%20intriguing%20connection%20appears%20towards%20the%20end%20when%20Piketty%20describes%20the%20present%20ideological%20cleavage%20in%20electoral%20democracies%20as%20between%20%E2%80%9CBrahmin%20left%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Cmerchant%20right%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0%20He%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20use%20the%20term%20Brahmin%20in%20such%20naming%20to%20refer%20to%20the%20function%20of%20the%20clergy%20or%20priestly%20class%20in%20the%20old%20ternary%20society%20or%20even%20its%20reconfiguration%20in%20the%20ownership%20society%20as%20a%20new%20set%20of%20cultural%20advantages%20genealogically%20derived.%20He%20uses%20it%20to%20point%20to%20the%20alienation%20of%20the%20left%20%E2%80%93%20as%20an%20educated%2C%20intellectual%20class%20%E2%80%93%20from%20the%20working%20class%20it%20is%20supposed%20to%20represent.%20This%20is%20more%20or%20less%20the%20reason%20why%20Ernsto%20Laclau%20and%20Chantal%20Mouffe%20appeal%20to%20the%20emergence%20of%20left%20populism%2C%20as%20DM%20rightly%20points%20to.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDM%20sets%20up%20the%20empirical%20and%20conceptual%20ground%20to%20pose%20the%20question%20of%20how%20far%20Dravidianism%20has%20succeeded%20in%20de-Brahminising%20the%20left%2C%20making%20redistribution%20the%20norm%20of%20populist%20reason.%20Dravidianism%20has%20also%20implicitly%20endorsed%20socialist-federalist%20global%20immanence%20as%20against%20the%20inegalitarian%20merchant%20nativism%20of%20nation-states%20in%20Piketty%E2%80%99s%20formulation.%20A%20combined%20reading%20of%20%3Cem%3EThe%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3EDravidian%20Model%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20%3Cem%3ECapital%20and%20Ideology%3C%2Fem%3E%20will%20hopefully%20energise%20future%20research%20into%20the%20ideological%20potential%20of%20Dravidianism.%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ERajan%20Kurai%20Krishnan%20teaches%20at%20Ambedkar%20University%2C%20Delhi.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689643829000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F17200916%2F18015946060_e7c39e240b_k.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fhow-the-dravidian-model-of-development-succeeded-in-tamil-nadu%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20prioritising%20the%20counter%20hegemonic%20articulations%20of%20the%20plebes%20against%20the%20exploitative%20Brahminical%20social%20order%2C%20Dravidianism%20evolved%20a%20new%20common%20sense%20of%20equity%20as%20the%20bedrock%20of%20popular%2C%20electoral%20democracy.%C2%A0%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A4%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fhow-the-dravidian-model-of-development-succeeded-in-tamil-nadu%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22What%20do%20we%20have%20to%20lose%20if%20Starlink%20satellites%20and%20others%20like%20them%20take%20over%20the%20night%20sky%3F%20Studying%20dark%20matter%2C%20observing%20distant%20galaxies%2C%20and%20finding%20signs%20of%20extraterrestrial%20intelligence.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224002%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Starlink%20train%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5fad8d6c1e8d500019813302%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223002%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E18%20April%202020%2C%20Brandenburg%2C%20Sieversdorf%3A%20Two%20%26quot%3BStarlink%26quot%3B%20satellites%20can%20be%20seen%20as%20stripes%20of%20light%20in%20the%20night%20sky%20(shot%20with%20an%20exposure%20time%20of%2015%20seconds).%3Cp%3EPatrick%20Pleul%2Fpicture%20alliance%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EA%20new%20study%20says%20that%20Elon%20Musk's%20constellation%20of%20broadband%20satellites%20is%20leaking%20radiation.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EUnintended%20emissions%20could%20affect%20the%20data%20that%20radio%20astronomers%20can%20collect%20accurately.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EExperts%20who%20spoke%20to%20Insider%20say%20radio%20astronomy%20helps%20us%20study%20dark%20matter%20and%20look%20for%20alien%20life.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ESpaceX's%20network%20of%20low-orbit%20satellites%20emits%20%26quot%3Bunintended%20electromagnetic%20radiation%26quot%3B%20that%20could%20negatively%20affect%20the%20study%20of%20deep%20space%2C%20a%20new%20paper%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20group%20of%20scientists%20from%20the%20Netherlands%20Institute%20of%20Radio%20Astronomy%20says%20they%20detected%20radiation%20onboard%2047%20out%20of%2068%20satellites%20observed%20over%20the%20course%20of%20an%20hour%2C%20according%20to%20a%20study%20published%20in%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aanda.org%2Fcomponent%2Farticle%3Faccess%3Ddoi%26doi%3D10.1051%2F0004-6361%2F202346374%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAstronomy%20%26amp%3B%20Astrophysics%2C%20a%20peer-reviewed%20journal.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Starlink%20satellites%20%E2%80%94%20chosen%20for%20their%20abundance%20in%20the%20sky%20compared%20to%20other%20low-orbit%20satellites%20%E2%80%94%20were%20observed%20using%20the%20Low-Frequency%20Array%20telescope%20in%20the%20Netherlands.%20The%20telescope%20is%20the%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.astron.nl%2Ftelescopes%2Flofar%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20largest%20in%20the%20world%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20consists%20of%2040%20radio%20antennas%20spread%20across%20Europe%20with%20the%20ability%20to%20observe%20wavelengths%20of%20radiation%20from%20the%20farthest%20regions%20of%20space.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUsing%20the%20telescope%2C%20scientists%20detected%20frequencies%20from%20the%20Starlink%20satellites%20at%20110%20to%20188%20megahertz%20%E2%80%94%20a%20unit%20of%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.merriam-webster.com%2Fdictionary%2Fmegahertz%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20measure%C2%A0used%20for%20electromagnetic%20waves%3C%2Fa%3E.%20This%20range%2C%20they%20noted%2C%20%26quot%3Bincludes%20a%20protected%20band%20between%20150.05%20and%20153%20MHz.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20protected%20band%2C%20allotted%20to%20radio%20astronomers%20specifically%20to%20study%20space%2C%20has%20scientists%20concerned%20that%20the%20radiation%20could%20affect%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnasa-james-webb-space-telescope-best-images-from-first-year-2022-12%5C%22%3Eobservations%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERepresentatives%20for%20SpaceX%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20Insider's%20request%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EVahe%20Peroomian%2C%20a%20University%20of%20Southern%20California%20professor%20of%20physics%20and%20astronomy%2C%20told%20Insider%20disruptions%20from%20the%20Starlink%20satellites%20would%20be%20comparable%20to%20a%20signal%20messing%20up%20the%20music%20from%20a%20radio%20station.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeroomian%20described%20it%20as%20someone%20deciding%20%26quot%3Bto%20fly%20a%20satellite%20over%20Los%20Angeles%20that%20every%20five%20minutes%20broadcasts%20at%20your%20favorite%20station's%20level%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20would%20operate%20under%20a%20specific%20frequency%20designated%20by%20the%20Federal%20Communications%20Commission.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAnd%20so%20as%20you're%20driving%20along%20listening%20to%20the%20radio%2C%20every%20five%20minutes%20you%20get%20half%20a%20minute%20of%20static%20in%20there%2C%26quot%3B%20Peroomian%20said.%20Instead%20of%20interrupting%20a%20song%2C%20however%2C%20these%20Starlink%20satellites%20are%20interrupting%20faint%20radio%20waves%20produced%20by%20astronomical%20objects.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20of%20the%20time%2C%20scientists%20who%20spoke%20to%20Insider%20noted%2C%20interfering%20frequencies%20are%20not%20as%20prevalent%20of%20an%20issue%20%E2%80%94%20although%20it%20is%20still%20encountered%20%E2%80%94%20because%20most%20radio%20telescopes%20are%20built%20in%20remote%20areas.%20However%2C%20Starlink%20and%20other%20low-orbit%20satellites%2C%20sometimes%20known%20as%20%26quot%3Bmegaconstellations%26quot%3B%20per%20the%20study%2C%20can%20travel%20wherever%20they%20choose%2C%20including%20over%20observational%20telescopes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFederico%20Di%20Vruno%2C%20one%20of%20the%20study%20co-authors%20and%20the%20co-director%20for%20the%20International%20Astronomical%20Union's%20Centre%20for%20the%20Protection%20of%20the%20Dark%20and%20Quiet%20Sky%20from%20Satellite%20Constellation%20Interference%2C%20told%20Insider%20there%20was%20a%20concern%20that%20as%20more%20low-orbit%20satellites%20are%20sent%20to%20space%2C%C2%A0these%20unintended%20emissions%20could%20be%20amplified%2C%20making%20it%20more%20difficult%20to%20use%20radio%20telescopes.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%20for%20space%2C%20as%20far%20as%20we%20understand%2C%20there%20is%20nothing%20out%20there%20that%20says%20this%20is%20the%20maximum%20level%20of%20unintended%20emissions%20that%20a%20satellite%20can%20have%2C%26quot%3B%20Di%20Vruno%20told%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ERadio%20astronomy%20helps%20research%20space's%20greatest%20mysteries%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EScientists%20and%20astronomers%20who%20spoke%20to%20Insider%20say%20that%20working%20around%20electrical%20signals%20when%20operating%20sensitive%20radio%20telescopes%20has%20always%20been%20challenging.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETake%2C%20for%20example%2C%20a%20multimillion-dollar%20Chinese%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wired.com%2Fstory%2Fchina-fast-worlds-largest-telescope-tourists%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eradio%20telescope%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20copes%20with%20the%20challenge%20of%20a%20nearby%20tourist%20town%20themed%20after%20the%20telescope%2C%20where%20astronomy%20enthusiasts%20use%20cell%20phones%2C%20WiFi%2C%20and%20other%20tech%20that%20may%20obscure%20electromagnetic%20emissions%20from%20light%20years%20away.%C2%A0Another%20example%20is%20the%20now-defunct%20Iridium%20satellite%20fleet%20of%20the%20nineties%2C%20which%20produced%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.science.org%2Fcontent%2Farticle%2Firidiums-loss-astronomers-gain%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estatic%20in%20a%20frequency%20used%20by%20radio%20astronomers%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20help%20scientists%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Facademic.oup.com%2Fmnras%2Farticle%2F277%2F1%2F210%2F1060737%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elearn%20how%20stars%20form%20and%20die%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BRadio%20telescopes%20are%20extremely%20sensitive%2C%26quot%3B%20Peroomian%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20build%20them%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20nowhere%20because%20cell%20phones%20and%20even%20microwave%20ovens%20could%20produce%20a%20signal%20that%20would%20interfere%20with%20their%20observations.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDi%20Vruno%20told%20Insider%20the%20total%20effect%20of%20low-orbit%20satellites%20like%20Starlink's%20on%20radio%20astronomy%20is%20not%20yet%20apparent.%20The%20team%2C%20he%20said%2C%20is%20hoping%20to%20include%20observations%20of%20celestial%20bodies%20in%20their%20next%20study%C2%A0and%2C%20for%20example%2C%20compare%20their%20observations%20to%20data%20collected%20before%20Starlink%20satellites%20began%20to%20crowd%20the%20night%20sky%20to%20see%20if%20they%20have%20changed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%26quot%3BWe%20are%20not%20saying%20that%20right%20now%20that%20radio%20astronomy%20is%20doomed%2C%20and%20that%20we%20will%20not%20be%20able%20to%20do%20astronomy%20anymore.%20We%20are%20saying%20it's%20important%20to%20recognize%20this%20early%20enough%20to%20have%20the%20discussions%20with%20operators%20with%20regulators%20with%20astronomy%2C%20to%20say%2C%20'Okay%2C%20this%20is%20a%20thing%20and%20we%20need%20to%20discuss%20it%20and%20move%20forward.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20the%20experts%20who%20spoke%20to%20Insider%2C%20however%2C%20said%20the%20loss%20or%20significant%20interference%20of%20radio%20astronomy%20would%20be%20a%20hindrance%20to%20scientists%20studying%20the%20existence%20of%20dark%20matter%2C%20the%20formation%20of%20stars%2C%20or%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nsf.gov%2Fnews%2Fspecial_reports%2Fastronomy%2Fepoch_reionization.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eepoch%20of%20reionization%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20a%20period%20starting%20400%20million%20years%20ago%20when%20the%20first%20stars%20and%20galaxies%20formed.%20There%20is%20also%20the%20financial%20loss%3A%20Millions%20of%20dollars%20go%20into%20planning%20and%20building%20these%20massive%20radio%20telescopes%20over%20decades.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJean-Luc%20Margot%2C%20a%20radio%20astronomer%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Southern%20California%2C%20Los%20Angeles%2C%20who%20leads%20an%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fseti.ucla.edu%2Fwp%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einitiative%20searching%20to%20identify%20technological%20signs%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0of%20extraterrestrial%20intelligence%2C%20told%20Insider%20that%20interference%20of%20radio%20astronomy%20could%20present%20an%20issue%20for%20his%20and%20other%20researchers'%20search%20for%20life%20in%20the%20universe%2C%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20would%20be%20a%20really%20phenomenal%20event%20in%20knowledge%20of%20the%20universe%20to%20know%20that%20we're%20not%20alone%20and%20there's%20a%20real%20possibility%20that%20radio%20frequency%20interference%20could%20prevent%20that%20detection%20from%20happening%2C%26quot%3B%20Margot%20told%20Insider.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPerhaps%20not%20the%20low-level%20emission%20that%20is%20studied%20in%20this%20paper%2C%20but%20other%20kinds%20of%20interference%2C%20like%20the%20intended%20emissions%20of%20a%20certain%20satellite%E2%80%A6imagine%20that%20there's%20an%20advanced%20civilization%20somewhere%20in%20the%20Milky%20Way%2C%20that%20that%20has%20a%20beacon%20to%20try%20to%20communicate%20with%20our%20civilization%20or%20any%20other%20civilization%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20continued%3A%20%26quot%3BIf%20that%20frequency%20happens%20to%20be%20overlapping%E2%80%A6we%20might%20not%20be%20able%20to%20detect%20it%20and%20that%20would%20be%20tragic%20not%20to%20be%20able%20to%20do%20that%2C%20to%20make%20that%20discovery.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDi%20Vruno%20told%20Insider%20the%20researchers%20have%20been%20collaborating%20with%20SpaceX%20engineers%2C%20the%20Elon%20Musk%20company%20that%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fspacex-starlink-internet-service-elon-musk-all-you-need-know-2021-2%5C%22%3E%20provides%20the%20nearly%204%2C000%20Starlink%20satellites%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20discuss%20ways%20to%20mitigate%20unintended%20radiation%20in%20the%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20over%20the%20next%20few%20years%2C%20Musk%20hopes%20to%20send%20thousands%20of%20new%20satellites%20above%20Earth%20and%20experts%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-elon-musk-42000-starlink-satellites-earth-effects-stars-2020-10%5C%22%3Ealready%20worried%20that%20this%20could%20create%20another%20problem%20for%20the%20observation%20of%20space%20by%20producing%20extreme%20light%20pollution%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20would%20affect%20optical%20telescopes.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-starlink-satellites-leaking-unintended-radiation-spacex-study-2023-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689642923000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5fad8d6c1e8d500019813302%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-starlink-satellites-leaking-unintended-radiation-spacex-study-2023-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%2247%20of%2068%20Starlink%20satellites%20observed%20produced%20unintentional%20radiation%20due%20to%20onboard%20electronics.%20Scientists%20suspect%20other%20satellites%20have%20the%20same%20issue.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22hgetahun%40insider.com%20(Hannah%20Getahun)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A52%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-starlink-satellites-leaking-unintended-radiation-spacex-study-2023-7%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Former%20Kerala%20CM%20Oommen%20Chandy%20passes%20away%20at%2079%22%2C%22con