2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Vienna%2C%20Austria%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64b5a6fddb9026001935587d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ESylvain%20Sonnet%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EVienna%2C%20Austria%2C%20has%20become%20the%20prime%20European%20city%20for%20spies%2C%20especially%20from%20Russia%2C%20to%20set%20up.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20country%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ft.com%2Fcontent%2Ff790d8f4-2fe1-466d-8b29-83b1f4956984%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehas%20no%20legislation%20banning%20espionage%3C%2Fa%3E%20unrelated%20to%20national%20affairs.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EEfforts%20by%20local%20politicians%20to%20ban%20spying%20have%20been%20met%20with%20delays%20as%20Russia's%20war%20continues.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ENearly%20a%20year%20and%20a%20half%20into%20Russia's%20war%20in%20Ukraine%2C%20Austria%20has%20expelled%20remarkably%20few%20Russian%20spies%20in%20comparison%20to%20its%20neighbors%2C%20as%20a%20coalition%20of%20MPs%20are%20urging%20their%20government%20to%20clamp%20down%20on%20espionage.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAustria's%20government%20has%20instead%20suspended%20two%20parliamentary%20votes%20on%20the%20matter%2C%20providing%20a%20ripe%20environment%20for%20continental%20and%20international%20spying%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ft.com%2Fcontent%2Ff790d8f4-2fe1-466d-8b29-83b1f4956984%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eper%20The%20Financial%20Times.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EVienna's%20longtime%20legal%20approach%20has%20been%20to%20ignore%20the%20espionage%20if%20it%20doesn't%20concern%C2%A0its%20own%20national%20affairs.%20And%20with%20the%20International%20Atomic%20Energy%20Agency%20and%20various%20international%20bodies%20based%20in%20the%20city%2C%20the%20lackadaisical%20attitude%20has%20posed%20a%20host%20of%20security%20problems.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAustria%20has%20expelled%20only%20four%20Russian%20spies%20posing%20as%20diplomats%2C%20while%20neighbors%20equipped%20with%20more%20robust%20laws%20have%20expelled%20over%20400%20spies%20since%20the%20start%20of%20Russia's%20war%2C%20the%20Times%20reported.%20There%20are%20180%20accredited%20Russian%20diplomats%20in%20Vienna%2C%20and%20a%20third%20of%20them%20are%20assumed%20to%20be%20spies%2C%20per%20the%20report.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20in%20July%202022%2C%20The%20Washington%20Post%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fnational-security%2F2022%2F07%2F05%2Faustria-russia-infuence%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20Egisto%20Ott%2C%20a%20former%20official%20in%20Austria's%20security%20services%20who%20managed%20undercover%20agents%2C%20was%20arrested%20on%20suspicion%20of%20selling%20state%20secrets%20to%20Russia.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20ongoing%20case%20shows%20the%20fine%20line%20between%20espionage%20that%20implicates%20Austria%2C%20and%20spying%20that%20uses%20Austria%20as%20a%20fertile%20ground%20while%20Russia's%20war%20in%20Ukraine%20rages%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BVienna%20is%20a%20perfect%20hub%20for%20spying%2C%20and%20always%20was%2C%26quot%3B%20Gustav%20Gressel%2C%20a%20senior%20policy%20fellow%20at%20the%20European%20Council%20on%20Foreign%20Relations%20and%20former%20Austrian%20military%20officer%2C%20told%20the%20Times.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20are%20a%20Russian%20intelligence%20officer%2C%20and%20you%20want%20to%20run%20a%20source%20in%20Germany%2C%20why%20would%20you%20run%20the%20risk%20of%20meeting%20him%20there%3F%20You%20invite%20this%20guy%20on%20a%20skiing%20holiday%20in%20Austria.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20conservative%20and%20Green%20party%20coalition%20in%20Austria%20has%20pushed%20for%20legislation%20that%20would%20ban%20spying%20%26quot%3Bagainst%20a%20foreign%20state%20or%20international%20organization%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20Vienna's%20unpopular%20government%20has%20twice%20called%20for%20more%20time%20to%20consider%20it%20before%20allowing%20a%20vote.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERecently%2C%20Chinese%2C%20Saudi%2C%20Iranian%20and%20Israeli%20spies%20have%20also%20benefitted%20from%20the%20power%20vacuum%20in%20Vienna%2C%20the%20Times%20reported.%20And%20some%20Western%20officials%20are%20monitoring%20the%20situation%2C%20with%20others%20getting%20in%20on%20the%20action.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20really%20is%20the%20Wild%20West%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20Western%20diplomat%20in%20Austria%20told%20the%20Times%20under%20the%20condition%20of%20anonymity.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20almost%20comical%20how%20much%20is%20being%20gotten%20away%20with%20here.%20Even%20from%20our%20side%2C%20I%20am%20sure.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fvienna-crawling-russian-spies-does-not-want-to-ban-them-2023-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689632470000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64b5a799db902600193558a3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fvienna-crawling-russian-spies-does-not-want-to-ban-them-2023-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Austrian%20government%2C%20unlike%20its%20neighbors%2C%20has%20mostly%20avoided%20attempts%20to%20criminalize%20espionage%20as%20Russia's%20war%20in%20Ukraine%20drags%20on.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22aharoun%40insider.com%20(Azmi%20Haroun)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A6%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fvienna-crawling-russian-spies-does-not-want-to-ban-them-2023-7%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Israel's%20workhorse%20Merkava%20tank%20could%20soon%20be%20refilling%20foreign%20arsenals%20depleted%20by%20the%20war%20in%20Ukraine%22%2C%22conte