ight%20given%20to%20each%20factor%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F17231903%2FPicture-1-Caption_-_-Indicators-in-calculatiing-India%25E2%2580%2599s-multipoverty-index-used-by-Niti-Aayog.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22696%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F17231903%2FPicture-1-Caption_-_-Indicators-in-calculatiing-India%25E2%2580%2599s-multipoverty-index-used-by-Niti-Aayog.png%20696w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F17231903%2FPicture-1-Caption_-_-Indicators-in-calculatiing-India%25E2%2580%2599s-multipoverty-index-used-by-Niti-Aayog-300x217.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-663675%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22504%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EIndicators%20used%20by%20Niti%20Aayog%20in%20calculating%20India%E2%80%99s%20multidimensional%20poverty%20index.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20deprivation%20score%20is%20the%20sum%20of%20the%20weighted%20status%20of%20all%20the%20indicators%20for%20an%20individual.%20If%20the%20deprivation%20score%20is%20more%20than%200.33%2C%20only%20then%20an%20individual%20is%20considered%20multidimensionally%20poor%2C%20even%20if%20s%2Fhe%20is%20poor%20as%20per%20some%20of%20the%20indicators.%200.33%20(or%2033%25)%20is%20considered%20the%20standard%20cutoff%20globally%2C%20the%20report%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ERecently%2C%20the%20UNDP%20released%20the%20global%20multidimensional%20poverty%20index.%20It%20released%20MPIs%20for%20all%20individual%20countries%20also.%20In%20the%20case%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhdr.undp.org%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2FCountry-Profiles%2FMPI%2FIND.pdf%3F_gl%3D1*xlmid7*_ga*MTkyNzc3ODAzNC4xNjg5NTg3MjQ0*_ga_3W7LPK0WP1*MTY4OTU4NzI0NC4xLjEuMTY4OTU4NzI2Ni4zOC4wLjA.%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EIndia%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%E2%80%93%20just%20like%20Niti%20Aayog%20%E2%80%93%20it%20also%20used%20NFHS-5%20data.%20However%2C%20according%20to%20the%20global%20MPI%2C%20or%20the%20percentage%20of%20people%20living%20in%20multidimensional%20poverty%2C%20in%20India%2016.4%20as%20compared%20to%2014.96%25%20of%20the%20Niti%20Aayog.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20difference%20of%201.44%25%20points%20is%20significant%20in%20absolute%20numbers%20considering%20India%E2%80%99s%20high%20population.%20In%20other%20words%2C%20another%2020%20million%20people%20of%20India%20are%20multidimensionally%20poor%20according%20to%20the%20UN%2C%20while%20Niti%20Aayog%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20think%20so.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMost%20of%20the%20indicators%20used%20for%20computing%20global%20MPI%20by%20the%20UN%20and%20national%20MPI%20by%20Niti%20Aayog%20are%20also%20the%20same.%20Except%20for%20the%20fact%20that%20Niti%20Aayog%20takes%20into%20account%20two%20more%20factors%C2%A0%20%E2%80%93%20maternal%20mortality%20and%20opening%20of%20the%20bank%20accounts%20(more%20on%20this%20later).%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMajor%20findings%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Niti%20Aayog%20report%20says%20that%20though%20there%20has%20been%20a%20decline%20in%20the%20incidence%20of%20poverty%2C%20the%20urban-rural%20divide%20still%20remains%20a%20matter%20of%20concern%20as%20the%20proportion%20of%20multidimensional%20poor%20was%2019.28%25%20of%20the%20Indian%20population%20while%20in%20urban%20areas%20it%20stood%20at%205.27%25%2C%20in%202019-21.%C2%A0%20As%20far%20as%20indicator-wise%20performance%20is%20concerned%2C%2031.52%25%20of%20the%20Indian%20population%20is%20still%20considered%20deprived%20as%20far%20as%20access%20to%20optimum%20nutrition%20services%20are%20concerned%2C%20in%20the%20current%20assessment%20%E2%80%93%20though%20the%20deprivation%20has%20come%20down%20by%20about%206%25%20points%20as%20compared%20to%20the%20previous%20one.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Union%20government%20ministers%20have%20on%20many%20occasions%20claimed%20that%20India%20has%20become%20open%20defecation%20free%20but%20this%20Niti%20Aayog%20report%20also%20showed%20that%2030.13%25%20of%20the%20population%20is%20deprived%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20sanitation%20services%20and%2043.90%25%20of%20people%20are%20deprived%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20access%20to%20cooking%20fuel.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fflo.uri.sh%2Fstory%2F1980206%2Fembed%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Interactive%20or%20visual%20content%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpublic.flourish.studio%2Fstory%2F1980206%2F%3Futm_source%3Dembed%26utm_campaign%3Dstory%2F1980206%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_top%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Made%20with%20Flourish%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpublic.flourish.studio%2Fresources%2Fmade_with_flourish.svg%5C%22%3E%20%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20the%20above%20charts%20showed%20the%20proportion%20of%20the%20population%20falling%20deprived%20vis-a-vis%20various%20indicators%2C%20if%20there%20is%20one%20indicator%20that%20has%20contributed%20the%20maximum%20to%20multidimensional%20poverty%2C%20it%20was%20clearly%20nutrition%2C%20the%20report%20showed.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20other%20words%2C%20which%20deprivations%20are%20making%20the%20poor%2C%20%E2%80%98poor%E2%80%99%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Lack%20of%20proper%20nutrition%20contributed%20to%20the%20tune%20of%2029.86%25%20in%20the%20calculation%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20multi-poverty%20index.%20%E2%80%9CContributing%20to%20nearly%20one-third%20of%20the%20multidimensional%20poverty%20in%20India%2C%20nutrition%20is%20arguably%20one%20of%20the%20most%20important%20indicators%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20national%20MPI%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20report%20says.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F02%2F17123202%2F108201-aeveizlzly-1544899613.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F02%2F17123202%2F108201-aeveizlzly-1544899613.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F02%2F17123202%2F108201-aeveizlzly-1544899613-300x158.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F02%2F17123202%2F108201-aeveizlzly-1544899613-1024x538.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-338592%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22630%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EChildren%20in%20an%20Odisha%20school%20eat%20their%20midday%20meal.%20Photo%3A%20mdmodisha.nic.in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20an%20indicator%2C%20lack%20of%20nutrition%20services%20was%20followed%20by%20lack%20of%20years%20of%20schooling%20(16.65%25)%2C%20inadequate%20access%20maternal%20health%20services%20(11.73%25)%2C%20less-than-desired%20school%20attendance%20(9.10%25)%2C%20lack%20of%20access%20to%20proper%20cooking%20fuel%20(8.82%25)%2C%20housing%20needs%20(8.65%25)%2C%20sanitation%20services%20(6.63%25)%2C%20ownership%20of%20assets%20(3.39%25)%20and%20the%20other%20factors%20whose%20contribution%20was%200-2%25.%20The%20other%20factors%20included%20child-adolescent%20mortality%20(1.48%25)%2C%20electricity%20(1.32%25)%2C%20drinking%20water%20(1.60%25)%20and%20bank%20account%20(0.78%25).%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20terms%20of%20the%20performance%20of%20states%2C%20Bihar%20has%20shown%20the%20highest%20reduction%20in%20multidimensional%20poverty%20in%20the%20current%20assessment%20vis-a-vis%20the%20last%20one.%20Although%20this%20should%20not%20come%20as%20a%20surprising%20finding%20because%20Bihar%20had%20the%20highest%20percentage%20of%20people%20living%20with%20multidimensional%20poverty%20across%20India.%20The%20following%20chart%20explains%20the%20status%20of%20states%20and%20the%20reduction%20of%20poverty%20between%20the%20two%20assessment%20periods%20of%20the%20Niti%20Aayog.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fflo.uri.sh%2Fvisualisation%2F14472469%2Fembed%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Interactive%20or%20visual%20content%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpublic.flourish.studio%2Fvisualisation%2F14472469%2F%3Futm_source%3Dembed%26utm_campaign%3Dvisualisation%2F14472469%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_top%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Made%20with%20Flourish%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpublic.flourish.studio%2Fresources%2Fmade_with_flourish.svg%5C%22%3E%20%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EStates%20and%20indicators%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20far%20as%20indicator-wise%20and%20state-wise%20performance%20is%20concerned%2C%20Bihar%2C%20with%2042.20%25%20of%20the%20population%20deprived%20of%20proper%20food%2C%20stood%20at%20the%20top%20of%20deprivation%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98nutrition%E2%80%99%20indicator.%20It%20was%20followed%20by%20Jharkhand%20(40.32%25)%2C%20Gujarat%20(38.09%25)%2C%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20(36.43)%2C%20and%20Chhattisgarh%20(35.12%25).%20According%20to%20the%20report%2C%20a%20woman%20of%2015%20to%2049%20years%20or%20a%20man%20of%2015%20to%2054%20years%20is%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Econsidered%20undernourished%20if%20their%20body%20mass%20index%20(BMI)%20is%20below%2018.5%20kg%2Fm2.%20The%20children%20under%20five%20years%20are%20considered%20malnourished%20if%20their%20z-score%20of%20height-for-age%20(stunting)%20or%20weight-for-age%20(underweight)%20is%20below%20minus%20two%20standard%20deviations%20from%20the%20median%20of%20the%20reference%20population.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20household%20is%20considered%20deprived%20as%20per%20%E2%80%98child%20and%20adolescent%20mortality%E2%80%99%20if%20any%20child%20or%20adolescent%20under%2018%20years%20of%20age%20has%20died%20in%20the%20household%20in%20the%20five-year%20period%20preceding%20the%20survey.%20Factors%20such%20as%20lack%20of%20access%20to%20healthcare%2C%20infectious%20diseases%2C%20malnutrition%2C%20iron%20deficiency%20(anemia)%2C%20or%20an%20unsafe%20environment%20are%20all%20contributors%20to%20child%20and%20adolescent%20mortality%2C%20the%20Niti%20Aayog%20report%20said%20quoting%20the%20WHO.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20death%20of%20a%20child%20or%20adolescent%20may%20therefore%20indicate%20the%20deprivations%20experienced%20by%20a%20household%20in%20one%20or%20more%20of%20these%20factors%2C%20the%20report%20says.%20In%20this%20indicator%20also%2C%20Bihar%20has%204.14%25%20of%20the%20population%20deprived%20%E2%80%93%20the%20highest.%20It%20is%20followed%20by%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20(3.54%25)%2C%20Meghalaya%20(2.99%25)%2C%20Jharkhand%20(2.57%25)%2C%20and%20Chhattisgarh%20(2.33%25).%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20household%20is%20considered%20deprived%20if%20any%20woman%20in%20the%20household%20who%20has%20given%20birth%20in%20the%20five%20years%20preceding%20the%20survey%20has%20not%20received%20at%20least%20four%20antenatal%20care%20visits%20for%20the%20most%20recent%20birth%20or%20has%20not%20received%20assistance%20from%20trained%20and%20skilled%20medical%20personnel%20during%20the%20most%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Erecent%20childbirth.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20factor%20is%20not%20included%20in%20the%20calculation%20of%20global%20MPI%20by%20the%20UN.%20Experts%20in%20India%20too%20have%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fpoverty-data-india-niti-aayog%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Equestioned%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20the%20inclusion%20of%20this%20factor%20in%20the%20MPI%20owing%20to%20the%20fact%20that%20almost%2080%25%20of%20deliveries%20in%20India%20are%20now%20%E2%80%98assisted%E2%80%99%20or%20take%20place%20in%20an%20institution%20like%20hospital.%20Therefore%2C%20since%20the%20performance%20under%20this%20indicator%20would%20be%20good%2C%20it%20would%20overall%20help%20in%20decreasing%20the%20MPI%2C%20offsetting%20the%20impact%20of%20other%20indicators.%20%5Bhyperlink%5D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20fact%2C%20studies%20like%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC9007995%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ethis%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3Ehave%20also%20shown%20that%20an%20increased%20institutional%20delivery%20rate%20didn%E2%80%99t%20translate%20into%20a%20proportionally%20better%20survival%20of%20newborns.%20%E2%80%9CThis%20analysis%20of%20191%2C963%20births%20in%20India%20found%20that%20without%20high-quality%20district%20health%20systems%2C%20health%20system%20coverage%20is%20insufficient%20to%20save%20newborn%20lives%E2%80%A6.Current%20policies%20and%20expenditure%20mostly%20aim%20at%20increasing%20institutional%20delivery.%20However%2C%20our%20findings%20indicate%20that%20they%20will%20fail%20to%20improve%20newborn%20survival%20where%20health%20system%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E%20quality%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3Efor%20maternity%20services%20is%20inadequate%E2%80%A6.%20These%20findings%20underscore%20the%20need%20to%20address%20both%20access%20and%20quality%20of%20health%20services%20in%20efforts%20to%20reduce%20the%20burden%20of%20avertable%20newborn%20deaths%2C%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%20the%20paper%20says.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENonetheless%2C%20Bihar%20topped%20the%20chart%20in%20terms%20of%20deprivation%20of%20this%20indicator%20with%2037.21%25%20of%20the%20population%20deprived.%20Meghalaya%20(31.3%25)%2C%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20(30.03%25)%2C%20Jharkhand%20(29.75%25)%20and%20Arunachal%20Pradesh%20(22.21%25)%20came%20next.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EUnder%20the%20%E2%80%98education%E2%80%99%20vertical%2C%20two%20factors%20have%20been%20considered%20%E2%80%93%20schooling%20and%20school%20attendance.%20A%20household%20is%20deprived%20if%20not%20even%20one%20member%20of%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ea%20household%20aged%2010%20years%20or%20older%20has%20completed%20six%20years%20of%20schooling.%20Bihar%20performed%20the%20worst%20followed%20by%20Meghalaya%2C%20Jharkhand%2C%20Andhra%20Pradesh%2C%20and%20Telangana.%20Similarly%2C%20a%20household%20is%20deprived%20if%20any%20school-aged%20child%20is%20not%20attending%20school%20up%20to%20the%20age%20at%20which%20he%2Fshe%20will%20complete%20class%208.%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20ranked%20top%20in%20terms%20of%20this%20deprivation%20followed%20by%20Bihar%2C%20Jharkhand%2C%20Meghalaya%20and%20Madhya%20Pradesh.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2017%2F07%2FPTI.gif%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Middle-aged%20children%20learning%20in%20a%20classroom.%20Credit%3A%20PTI%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22621%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-158279%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22381%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ERepresentational%20image.%20Photo%3A%20PTI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EUnder%20the%20%E2%80%98standard%20of%20living%E2%80%99%20vertical%2C%20seven%20indicators%20have%20been%20taken%20into%20account.%20If%20a%20household%20does%20not%20have%20%E2%80%98exclusive%E2%80%99%20access%20(non-shared)%20to%20any%20kind%20of%20toilet%2C%20it%20would%20be%20considered%20deprived%20under%20the%20%E2%80%98sanitation%E2%80%99%20indicator.%20In%20Bihar%2C%2050.78%25%20of%20the%20population%20does%20not%20have%20the%20requisite%20access.%20Jharkhand%20(43.36%25)%2C%20Odisha%20(39.85%25)%2C%20Madhya%20Pradesh%20(35.51%25)%20and%20Manipur%20(35.23%25)%20figured%20next%20in%20decreasing%20order.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20household%20is%20deprived%20under%20the%20category%20of%20%E2%80%98cooking%20fuel%E2%80%99%20if%20the%20primary%20source%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Efuel%20is%20dung%2C%20agricultural%20crops%2C%20shrubs%2C%20wood%2C%20charcoal%2C%20or%20coal.%20Jharkhand%20had%20the%20highest%20percentage%20of%20the%20population%20deprived%20%E2%80%93%2069.12%25%20%E2%80%93%20under%20this%20indicator.%20It%20was%20followed%20by%20Meghalaya%2C%20Chhattisgarh%2C%20Odisha%20and%20Bihar.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFor%20a%20household%20not%20to%20be%20considered%20deprived%20as%20per%20the%20%E2%80%98drinking%20water%E2%80%99%20indicator%2C%20it%20should%20have%20access%20to%20a%20source%20of%20safe%20drinking%20water%20or%20safe%20drinking%20water%20is%20more%20than%20a%2030-minute%20walk%20from%20home%20(as%20a%20round%20trip).%20In%20this%20indicator%2C%20the%20deprivation%20seemed%20relatively%20lesser%20worse%20as%20compared%20to%20others.%20Manipur%20fared%20the%20worst%20for%20this%20indicator%20with%2026.77%25%20people%20considered%20deprived%20as%20per%20the%C2%A0%20Niti%20Aayog%20definition.%20Meghalaya%2C%20Madhya%20Pradesh%2C%20Jharkhand%20and%20Assam%20come%20after%20Manipur%20in%20the%20decreasing%20order.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIf%20a%20household%20has%20no%20electricity%2C%20it%20would%20be%20considered%20deprived.%20This%20is%20one%20parameter%20on%20which%20some%20of%20the%20worst-performing%20states%2C%20as%20per%20the%20last%20assessment%2C%20seem%20to%20have%20made%20a%20huge%20comeback%3B%C2%A0%20at%20least%20on%20paper.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EConsider%20Uttar%20Pradesh.%20For%20the%20previous%20assessment%20period%2C%2027.43%25%20of%20the%20population%20was%20deprived.%20Now%2C%20the%20corresponding%20figure%20stands%20at%20only%209.16%25.%20Similar%20is%20the%20story%20of%20Bihar%20where%2039.86%25%20of%20the%20population%20was%20deprived%20of%20electricity%20in%202015-16%2C%20and%20in%202019-21%2C%20only%203.67%25%20of%20the%20population%20did%20not%20have%20access%20to%20electricity.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFor%20housing%20needs%2C%20a%20household%20has%20to%20have%20a%20floor%20and%20roof%20%E2%80%93%20both%20%E2%80%93%20not%20made%20of%20any%20rudimentary%20materials%20like%20mud%2C%20clay%20or%20dung%2C%20to%20be%20not%20considered%20deprived.%20Manipur%2C%20with%C2%A0%2075.50%25%20of%20the%20population%20not%20having%20access%20to%20a%20pucca%20house%20fared%20worst%20followed%20by%20Arunachal%20Pradesh%20(74.34%25)%2C%20Assam%20(69.37%25)%2C%20Tripura%20(66.83%25)%20and%20Bihar%20(65.37%25)%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBank%20account%20is%20yet%20another%20indicator%20under%20the%20standard%20of%20living%20vertical.%20This%20indicator%20also%20does%20not%20form%20part%20of%20the%20UN%E2%80%99s%20global%20MPI%20calculations.%20The%20Niti%20Aayog%20report%20showed%20a%20large%20part%20of%20the%20population%20has%20a%20bank%20account.%20With%20just%209.01%25%20of%20the%20population%20not%20having%20a%20bank%20account%2C%20Meghalaya%20became%20the%20worst%20performing%20state.%20Overall%2C%20as%20per%20Niti%20report%2C%2096%25%20people%20in%20India%20have%20bank%20accounts%20with%20only%204%25%20population%20deprived%20of%20them.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20experts%20have%20questioned%20the%20mere%20existence%20of%20a%20bank%20account%20as%20a%20development%20indicator%20for%20the%20calculation%20of%20MPI%20because%20existence%20of%20a%20bank%20account%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20necessarily%20lead%20to%20financial%20inclusion.%20Reports%20like%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.findevgateway.org%2Fblog%2F2022%2F11%2Fwhat-findex-2021-tells-us-about-financial-inclusion-india%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ethis%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20show%20that%20the%20ownership%20of%20bank%20accounts%20have%20stagnated%20during%20the%20pandemic%20years%2C%20ownership%20of%20debit%2Fcredit%20cards%20has%20decreased%20and%20fewer%20people%20are%20saving%20in%20financial%20institutions.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20last%20indicator%20is%20%E2%80%98asset%20ownership%E2%80%99.%20The%20household%20is%20deprived%20if%20it%20does%20not%20own%20more%20than%20one%20of%20these%20assets%3A%20radio%2C%20TV%2C%20telephone%2C%20computer%2C%20animal%20cart%2C%20bicycle%2C%20motorbike%2C%20or%20refrigerator%2C%20and%20does%20not%20own%20a%20car%20or%20truck.%20In%20Meghalaya%2C%2037.07%25%20of%20the%20population%20didn%E2%80%99t%20have%20the%20required%20ownership.%20People%20in%20Nagaland%2C%20Bihar%2C%20Madhya%20Pradesh%20and%20Jharkhand%20figured%20next%2C%20in%20decreasing%20order%2C%20as%20far%20as%20lack%20of%20ownership%20of%20the%20assets%20was%20concerned.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689620452000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F12%2F25110226%2F2020_6img03_Jun_2020_PTI03-06-2020_000296B.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2F20-79-crore-indians-are-poor-urban-rural-divide-a-concern-niti-aayog%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22While%20Niti%20Aayog's%20latest%20Multidimensional%20Poverty%20Index%20(MPI)%20considers%2014.96%25%20of%20India's%20population%20as%20poor%2C%20the%20recently%20released%20MPI%20by%20UNDP%20put%20the%20figure%20at%2016.4%25%2C%20based%20almost%20on%20the%20same%20indicators.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A4%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2F20-79-crore-indians-are-poor-urban-rural-divide-a-concern-niti-aayog%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%E2%80%98Yellowstone%E2%80%99