mpunity%E2%80%9D%20and%20activists%20claim%20that%20the%20legislation%20is%20being%20used%20by%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20government%2C%20which%20runs%20the%20union%20territory%20directly%2C%20to%20undermine%20the%20fundamental%20right%20of%20free%20speech%20in%20J%26amp%3BK.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETwo%20similarly%20worded%20orders%20were%20also%20issued%20by%20the%20GAD%20on%20Sunday%20to%20terminate%20Arshid%20Ahmad%20Thoker%2C%20a%20Constable%20in%20J%26amp%3BK%20Police%20who%20hails%20from%20Shopian%20district%2C%20and%20Murawath%20Hussain%20Mir%2C%20a%20native%20of%20Pulwama%20district%20who%20worked%20as%20%E2%80%98Wasil%20Baqi%20Navees%E2%80%99%20in%20J%26amp%3BK%E2%80%99s%20Revenue%20Department.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAll%20three%20employees%20have%20been%20dismissed%20by%20invoking%20sub-clause%20(c)%20of%20clause%20(2)%20of%20Article%20311%20which%20removes%20a%20critical%20safeguard%20of%20inquiry%20for%20the%20employees%20who%20are%20dismissed%20by%20the%20administration%20without%20any%20notice%20or%20a%20chance%20of%20representation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20sub-clause%20(c)%20rules%20out%20the%20opportunity%20for%20employees%20to%20contest%20the%20dismissal%20as%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20President%20or%20the%20Governor%2C%20as%20the%20case%20may%20be%2C%20is%20satisfied%20that%20in%20the%20interest%20of%20the%20security%20of%20the%20State%2C%20it%20is%20not%20expedient%20to%20hold%20such%20inquiry%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFaheem%2C%20who%20graduated%20from%20the%20University%20of%20Kashmir%E2%80%99s%20Media%20Education%20Research%20Department%20in%202008%2C%20worked%20with%20Srinagar-based%20and%20J%26amp%3BK%E2%80%99s%20largest%20English%20daily%2C%20%3Cem%3EGreater%20Kashmir%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20as%20an%20editor%20and%20a%20columnist.%20He%20was%20appointed%20as%20the%20varsity%E2%80%99s%20PRO%20in%20the%20same%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESon%20of%20a%20retired%20Kashmir%20University%20professor%2C%20Faheem%E2%80%99s%20columns%20in%20%3Cem%3EGreater%20Kashmir%3C%2Fem%3E%20focused%20on%20current%20affairs%2C%20in%20which%20he%20often%20criticised%20governments%20%E2%80%93%20from%20Omar%20Abdullah%20to%20Mehbooba%20Mufti%20and%20the%20Union%20government%2C%20for%20mishandling%20the%20situation%20in%20J%26amp%3BK.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMurawat%20joined%20the%20government%20as%20a%20junior%20assistant%20in%20the%20revenue%20department%20in%201985%20while%20Arshad%20was%20appointed%20as%20a%20constable%20in%20J%26amp%3BK%20Police%E2%80%99s%20armed%20wing%20in%202006%20and%20inducted%20in%20executive%20wing%20in%202009.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESeveral%20media%20reports%20alleged%20that%20the%20three%20employees%20were%20dismissed%20for%20%E2%80%9Cactively%20working%20with%20Pakistani%20terror%20outfits%E2%80%9D%2C%20%E2%80%9Cproviding%20logistics%20to%20terrorists%E2%80%9D%2C%20%E2%80%9Cpropagating%20terrorist%20ideology%E2%80%9D%2C%20%E2%80%9Craising%20terror%20finances%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Cfurthering%20secessionist%20agenda.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20there%20was%20no%20such%20reference%20in%20the%20official%20termination%20orders.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20the%20Modi%20government%20took%20charge%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20in%202019%20when%20Article%20370%20was%20read%20down%2C%20more%20than%2050%20employees%20have%20been%20terminated%20from%20service%20by%20the%20Union%20territory%20administration%20using%20Article%20311.%20Six%20of%20the%20dismissed%20employees%20are%20from%20Jammu%20while%20the%20rest%20are%20from%20Kashmir.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20reports%2C%20several%20dozen%20more%20employees%20are%20being%20probed%20for%20their%20alleged%20affiliation%20with%20militants%20and%20Kashmiri%20separatists.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20termination%20of%20the%20employees%20is%20part%20of%20a%20wider%20crackdown%20on%20what%20the%20Modi%20government%20has%20described%20as%20an%20%E2%80%9Cecosystem%20of%20terrorism%E2%80%9D%20in%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir.%20However%2C%20activists%20claim%20that%20the%20government%20is%20abusing%20the%20law%20to%20prevent%20any%20criticism%20of%20its%20policies%20ever%20since%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20was%20bifurcated%20and%20downgraded%20into%20two%20union%20territories.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202021%2C%C2%A0%C2%A0a%20%E2%80%98Special%20Task%20Force%E2%80%99%20was%20set%20up%20with%20members%20from%20J%26amp%3BK%E2%80%99s%20home%20and%20law%2C%20justice%20and%20parliamentary%20affairs%20departments%20by%20the%20J%26amp%3BK%20administration%20to%20screen%20employees%20and%20prepare%20a%20list%20of%20those%20who%20are%20suspected%20of%20involvement%20in%20%E2%80%9Canti-national%20activities%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESources%20said%20that%20the%20list%20is%20prepared%20after%20scrutinising%20the%20educational%20and%20family%20background%20of%20the%20employees%20and%20it%20is%20then%20referred%20to%20a%20committee%20headed%20by%20J%26amp%3BK%E2%80%99s%20chief%20secretary.%20The%20committee%20sends%20the%20list%20to%20the%20Lieutenant%20Governor%E2%80%99s%20office%20for%20action%20under%20Article%20311.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUsing%20Article%20311%2C%20the%20J%26amp%3BK%20administration%20has%20terminated%20teachers%2C%20doctors%2C%20revenue%20officials%2C%20police%20personnel%20and%20others.%20The%20targeted%20employees%20are%20accused%20of%20vague%20charges%20which%20have%20neither%20been%20specified%20to%20them%20nor%20shared%20with%20the%20media.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20administration%20has%20also%20empowered%20itself%20to%20prematurely%20retire%20employees%20%E2%80%9Cin%20the%20public%20interest%E2%80%9D%20for%20%E2%80%9Cnon-performance%2C%20misbehaviour%20or%20bad%20conduct%E2%80%9D%20by%20amending%20Article%20225%20(2)%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20Civil%20Service%20Regulations%201956.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20March%203%2C%202021%2C%20the%20administration%20made%20verification%20by%20the%20Criminal%20Investigations%20Department%2C%20J%26amp%3BK%E2%80%99s%20counter-intelligence%20agency%2C%20mandatory%20for%20new%20entrants%20into%20government%20service%2C%20while%20passports%20are%20also%20being%20denied%20to%20employees%20who%20don%E2%80%99t%20obtain%20clearance%20from%20J%26amp%3BK%E2%80%99s%20vigilance%20department.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20September%2016%2C%202021%2C%20the%20administration%20issued%20an%20order%20for%20%E2%80%9Cperiodic%20verification%E2%80%9D%20of%20all%20its%20employees%20and%20the%20Criminal%20Investigation%20Department%20was%20asked%20to%20deny%20clearances%20to%20employees%20involved%20in%20%E2%80%9Csabotage%2C%20espionage%2C%20treason%2C%20terrorism%2C%20subversion%2C%20sedition%2Fsecession%2C%20facilitating%20foreign%20interference%2C%20incitement%20to%20violence%20or%20any%20other%20unconstitutional%20act.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20order%20also%20asked%20the%20officials%20to%20deny%20clearance%20to%20employees%20whose%20relatives%20have%20%E2%80%9Cassociation%20or%20sympathy%20with%20persons%20who%20are%20attempting%20to%20commit%20any%20of%20the%20above%20acts%20or%20involved%20in%20aiding%20or%20abetting%20or%20advocating%20the%20above%20acts.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBefore%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20was%20bifurcated%20and%20downgraded%20into%20two%20Union%20territories%20on%20August%205%2C%202019%2C%20Article%20311%20was%20not%20applicable%20to%20the%20erstwhile%20state.%20However%2C%20successive%20governments%20used%20Section%20126%20of%20J%26amp%3BK%E2%80%99s%20Constitution%20to%20dismiss%20employees%20who%20were%20also%20provided%20safeguards%2C%20like%20in%20Article%20311.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689610859000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F09%2F01180244%2FEfZRdMaU0AAfEzt.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fj-activists-dub-move-as-arbitrary%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Article%20311%20of%20the%20constitution%20%E2%80%93%20which%20has%20been%20described%20as%20an%20instrument%20of%20'executive%20impunity'%20by%20the%20civil%20soc